Commentary.Commentary: We are back for the final session of Day 1! The players have made their way out to the middle. Dimuth Karunaratne and Kusal Mendis to open the batting for Sri Lanka. Jasprit Bumrah will start proceedings with the ball. Three slips and a gully in place. Here we go...
... Day 1, Session 3 ...

Ravichandran Ashwin, Ravindra Jadeja and Axar Patel will be smelling blood on this pitch. The dew might just kick in but the pitch might still assist them. Sri Lanka have to play bold here. The last and final session will start at 7.10 pm IST (1.40 pm GMT). Do join us then!

What an exceptional knock from Shreyas Iyer! He and Rishabh Pant made the spinners change their lengths and play against the pitch. Just too many short balls and Iyer did not hang back defending it. India's innings was mostly bolstered by Shreyas Iyer, who was playing so well on this tricky pitch. After a loose start by the openers. Virat Kohli and Hanuma Vihari did well to build the innings but both fell after getting a start. Rishabh Pant played in his own style and scored a quick 39 off 26 deliveries. It was Shreyas Iyer's innings that helped India brisk away in this session. He will be gutted to have not scored a century but nevertheless, it was one of the finest knocks on a pitch where others struggled.

If the pitch was bowling friendly, Shreyas Iyer made it his best friend. 252 looks a very, very good score on this pitch and India will be very happy going into the break after being hanging at 93/4 at the start of this session. On a pitch that was tricky to bat on, one would feel that Sri Lanka did not bowl to the best of their abilities. On this surface, the spinners are always handy but the trio - Lasith Embuldeniya, Dhananjaya de Silva and Praveen Jayawickrama bowled far too loose deliveries and gave away free boundaries. This might just be a pleasing score from India's point of view, knowing the face that they have much more experienced spinners than their opposition.

OUT! STUMPED! Praveen Jayawickrama has the last laugh and Iyer falls just 8 runs short of what could have been one of the finest knocks played on a turning track. Shreyas Iyer skips down the track and looks to go big. Praveen Jayawickrama serves a loopy ball, outside leg that turns away from the batter. Iyer misses his slog and the ball goes through to the keeper. Niroshan Dickwella collects the ball and whips the bails off. Iyer had no chance of getting back in the crease. India are bowled out for 252. That will be Dinner on Day 1!
Commentary.Howout: st Niroshan Dickwella b Praveen Jayawickrama

Commentary.Commentary: Full and on middle. Shreyas Iyer flicks it towards deep mid-wicket and takes a single.
A yorker-length ball, around middle. Shreyas Iyer fails to dig it out and gets hit low on his pad. The ball rolls to the slip fielder.
Flatter ball, down leg. Shreyas Iyer shuffles across to scoop it but he fails to get any bat on it.
Top effort from Lakmal in the deep! Tossed up, around off. Iyer skips down and carves it through cover. Lakmal puts in a dive in the deep and saves a couple of runs.
Lasith Embuldeniya comes over the wicket and serves a length ball, around off. Iyer keeps it out.
SIX! BOOM! Iyer is enjoying his time out in the middle! Tossed up, on off. Iyer clears his front leg and lofts it over long off to bag a maximum.
Review! Another LBW review taken upstairs. The replay shows an inside edge and it is confirmed by the UltraEdge as well. Bumrah survives for the second time.

NOT OUT! Inside edge saves Bumrah yet again! This is a tossed up delivery, around middle. Bumrah gets forward to defend but he gets an inside edge onto his pad. Dimuth Karunaratne opts for a review but he loses it as the UltraEdge shows a clear deviation as the ball passes the bat. The on-field decision remains.
Tosses it up, around middle. Jasprit Bumrah blocks it with soft hands.
Floated, around off. Bumrah defends it off the front foot.
Kusal Mendis is off the field and Chamika Karunaratne comes in as a substitute.  Kusal Mendis is holding his shoulder as he walks out.

DROPPED! Tosses it up, on off. Iyer advances down the track and looks to go downtown. He miscues it high in the air towards long off. Kusal Mendis runs across to his right from the deep, puts in a dive but he puts it down. The batters take a run.
Floated, full and around off. Iyer blocks it with ease.
Full and outside off. Shreyas Iyer drags it to long off and doesn't run.
Review! Sri Lanka have taken a review for LBW! UltraEdge shows the bat and ball is together but there is an inside edge.

NOT OUT! Slower through the air, on a length, around off. Bumrah blocks it. Sri Lanka opt for a review as they think that the ball hit the pad first. The replays roll in and the Ball Tracker shows that there was a clear inside edge. Sri Lanka lose another review.
Tossed up, around off. Bumrah keeps it out.
Flatter and quicker, around middle. Shreyas Iyer nudges it to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Floated, around middle. Iyer skips down and pushes it to long on. Iyer doesn't take the single.
On a length, outside off. Shreyas Iyer cuts it towards point.
FOUR! A half-tracker, around middle. Iyer rocks back and pulls it wide of long on for a boundary. He moves into the 80s now!
This is darted on the pads. Iyer flicks it to deep mid-wicket and takes a single.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Shreyas Iyer keeps it out.
SIX! BANG! Iyer means business! This is tossed up, around off. Iyer steps out a bit and smacks it over the bowler's head for a biggie.
A loopy ball, on a length, around off. Iyer hangs back and keeps it out in the end.
Iyer steps out so Praveen Jayawickrama drags his length back, around middle. Iyer tucks it to mid-wicket.
A quicker ball, outside off. Iyer cuts it towards deep backward point and does not take a run.
This is a loopy ball, well outside off. Bumrah leaves it watchfully.
Floated, full and around off. Bumrah stretches forward and defends it.
This is on a length, around off. Bumrah dabs it onto the deck.
Tossed up, outside off. Jasprit Bumrah leaves it alone.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Iyer cuts it wide of deep cover and manages only a single. Iyer is not happy with his judgement here!
A short ball, outside off. Iyer cuts it to deep cover without much timing. No run taken.
Tossed up, around off. Jasprit Bumrah keeps it out.
Jasprit Bumrah is the last batter in.

OUT! TAKEN! A soft dismissal and Shami would be gutted as this ball should have been parked out of the stadium! A short ball, around off. Shami swivels and looks to pull hard but the ball hurries onto him. It takes the top edge and goes in the air on the off side. Dhananjaya de Silva calls for it from the gully region. He runs forward and takes it with ease.
Commentary.Howout: c Dhananjaya de Silva b Praveen Jayawickrama

Commentary.Commentary: DROPPED! A tough one though! Flatter and quicker, around off. Iyer tries to cut but it goes off the outside edge towards the slip fielder who puts it down. The ball goes past him for a single.
This is darted on the pads. Shami nudges it behind square on the leg side and takes a single.
Flatter ball, going on with the angle from middle. Shami looks to flick but he misses and gets hit on his pad.
FOUR! Poor start from Jayawickrama! A half-tracker, around off, Shami rocks back and pulls it wide of mid on for a boundary. He is off the mark now!
Flatter and quicker, around off. Iyer taps it towards cover but does not manage to retain the strike for the next over.

Edged but safe! Flatter ball, on a length, around off and spinning away from the batter. Iyer tries to defend it with soft hands but it takes the outside edge and races away past the slip fielder for a brace.
Floated, on a length, around middle. Iyer skips down the track and defends it back to the bowler.
A quicker ball, around middle. Iyer tucks it to mid-wicket.
An overpitched ball, around off. Iyer digs it out towards cover.
Flatter and quicker, around middle. Shreyas Iyer stays back and keeps it out.
Back of a length, angling in from middle. Shami misses his flick and the ball goes towards fine leg after brushing his pad.
Good-length ball, around off. Mohammed Shami stays back and defends it towards cover.
Back of a length, outside off. Iyer works it towards deep point and takes a single this time.
A full ball, angling around the pads. Iyer glances it towards the fine leg fielder who stops it with a slide. No run taken.
A slower ball, into the surface, around leg. Iyer tickles it to fine leg and does not take a run.
Good-length ball, around off. Iyer hangs back to block it.

DROPPED! Tosses it up, on a length, outside off and spinning away late. Shami stays back and looks to poke at it. It takes the outside edge and Dhananjaya de Silva at second slip fails to gather it. The ball goes past him but the batters do not run.
A quicker ball, going on with the arm from middle. Mohammed Shami keeps it out.
Floated, full and outside off. Shreyas Iyer drills it to long off for a single.
An arm ball, going on with the angle, down leg. Shreyas Iyer misses his flick and the keeper fails to grab it.
Full and on off. Iyer blocks it out.
FOUR! SMASHED! This is tossed up, down leg. Shreyas Iyer kneels and sweeps it behind square on the leg side for a boundary.
Mohammed Shami is the new batter in.

OUT! BOWLED! Smart thinking from Suranga Lakmal! He comes over the wicket and serves a length ball, angling around off. Patel looks to cut it but gets cramped for the room. The ball takes the inside edge and rolls back onto the stump. Another Indian batter looking to cut the ball, fails in his action.
Commentary.Howout: b Suranga Lakmal

Commentary.Commentary: Length and on middle. Defended out.
Length ball, on off. Patel guides it to point.
Lakmal continues to bowl on the leg side. Iyer flicks it to deep square leg for one.
FOUR! Change of bowling but boundaries are constant. Again on the pads. Iyer tickles it fine to the fine leg fence.
A length ball, down the leg side. Iyer misses his flick.
Suranga Lakmal (6-3-6-0) is back on.
Half-tracker, outside off. Iyer on the back foot, cuts it to deep point for a single.
FOUR! Slightly short and on off. This time Iyer pulls it wide of mid-wicket for a boundary.
On middle. Blocked out.

Is that dropped? Yes, it was a hard one! Shorter and around off. Iyer stays on his back foot, pulls it flat and to the right of the fielder at mid-wicket and Charith Asalanka there, dives but fails to catch it.
Outside off. Patel punches it to deep point for a single.
SIX! Patel in the groove! Too many short deliveries today from the spinners. Patel rocks back and pulls it over mid-wicket for a biggie. 200 up as well.

SIX! Fifty for Shreyas Iyer! On a pitch that is friendly to the bowlers, he is showing his class. Fuller and on off. Iyer skips down and thumps it over cow corner for a maximum. He removes his helmet and takes all the applause from the crowd and his teammates.
Another single as Patel drills it to long off.
Now stays back and pushes it to point for a single.
SIX! Hammered! Tossed up, full and on off. Iyer dances down the track and heaves it over mid-wicket for a biggie.
Full and outside off. Patel drags it to mid-wicket for a single.
Axar Patel walks out to bat.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Short ball, outside off. Ashwin looks to guide it to third man as he opens the face of the bat but the ball stays low and takes the outside edge before meeting the keepers' gloves. Good catch by Niroshan Dickwella. India 7 down now.
Commentary.Howout: c Niroshan Dickwella b Dhananjaya de Silva

Commentary.Commentary: Floated, on middle, steep bounce and Iyer gets inside the line to keep it out.
A single as this is hit to square leg.
Bye! Down the leg side. Iyer misses his sweep. The keeper fumbled and a bye is taken.
Review! Sri Lanka review for a caught behind! The replays roll in and the UltraEdge suggests that there is no bat involved. The on-field decision stands.

NOT OUT! Short again, but this one just slides back in. Iyer looks to cut but misses. Niroshan Dickwella is confident as he appeals and after the decision goes against him, he asks to take it upstairs. Nothing on UltraEdge. Sri Lanka lose a review!
Shorter and outside off, cut away to deep point for a single.

An arm ball, slanting on the pads. Iyer misses his flick and it goes off the pads to fine leg. There is an appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved. Lahiru Thirimanne gives a chase to fine leg, slides and just when he tries to flick it back, his legs touch the ropes but no conclusive and three leg byes are taken.

DRINKS! India have done well to keep the scoreboard ticking and the Lankan spinners have been a bit inconsistent with their lines and lengths post Tea. Sri Lanka need to make sure that they wrap things up quickly and the hosts do not run away with the first innings score. The ball is turning square and India will be looking to go past the 200-run mark without losing any more wickets!
Very full and on off. Another solid defense from Ashwin.
Tossed up, on middle. Kept out.
On middle, flicked straight to leg slip.
Tossed up, full and landing outside off. Ashwin steps across and looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pad. An appeal but nothing given. Impact was outside off.
Fuller and on middle, drilled to long on for a single.
Two byes! Fuller ball, angling down and spinning away as well. Iyer leaves it and there is not much the keeper can do. The fielder gives a chase and does well to save a couple of runs.
Fuller and on middle. Ashwin flicks it to deep square leg for a couple of runs. The throw hits Iyer and the ball rolls away but Iyer denies the extra run. Fair play.
On middle. Blocked out.
Half-tracker, outside off and turning away. Ashwin misses his cut.
Flatter and angling on leg. Ashwin gets down the track and looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad. The ball rolls to fine leg and Iyer looks for a single but is sent back.
Shorter and outside off, cut away to deep point for a single.
On off, pushed to covers.
This one comes with the arm, on middle. Ashwin dead bats it.
Tossed up, on middle. Iyer wrists it to mid on for a single.
Fuller and on off. Defended.
On middle, fuller, floated as well. Iyer bunts it to mid-wicket and takes a couple of runs. The throw comes at the bowler's end and there is a misfield but no extra run is taken.
Fuller and outside off, driven to deep point for a single.
FOUR! A full toss, on  middle. Ashwin whips it in the gap through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Angles it on the pads. Iyer mistimes his flick.
A loopy ball, on midde. Iyer gets low to defend but it takes the inside edge and rolls to fine leg.
Tossed up again, outside off. Iyer keeps it out on the off side.
Fuller and on off. Iyer drives it to covers.
On middle. Blocked out.
Around off, punched off the back foot to covers.
Tossed up, given much flight, on middle. Ashwin comes forward to defend but gets an outside edge, just short of the gully fielder.
On middle. Shreyas reaches to the pitch of the ball and pushes it to mid off for a single.
FOUR! Iyer plants his front foot forward and Praveen Jayawickrama drags his length back. Iyer rocks back and whacks it to square leg for a boundary.
An arm ball, on middle. Defended.
On the pads, tucked to deep square leg for one.
Tossed up, outside off and turning away late. Ashwin skips down and looks to drive but gets an outside edge to point.
Short and around off, extra bounce and Iyer works it on the leg side.
Flatter and spinning away, outside off. Blocked out.
Short ball, on off. Iyer taps it on top of the bounce, back to the bowler.
Around off, pushed to point.
FOUR! very nicely played! Shorter, slower in the air and outside off. Iyer opens the face of the bat and guides it late past point for a boundary.
A full ball, angling down the leg side. Iyer comes down the track and flicks it to deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Floated, full and outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin lets it through to the keeper. A maiden over from Praveen Jayawickrama!
A low full toss, around off. Ravichandran Ashwin drags it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Tossed up, on a length, just outside off and spinning away late. Ravichandran Ashwin prods to defend but the ball spins past his outside edge.
Floated, full and on middle. Ravichandran Ashwin pushes it back to the bowler.
An overpitched ball, around off. Ravichandran Ashwin drags it back to the bowler.
Flighted ball, around off. Ravichandran Ashwin dabs it onto the deck, off the front foot.
Slower through the air, on a length, around off. Shreyas Iyer gets forward and defends it.
Around off, blocked out.
Full and on off. Ashwin skips down the track and pushes it to the off side for a single.
Tossed up, around off. Ravichandran Ashwin blocks it out.
Review! Ashwin takes the LBW decision upstairs. UltraEdge shows no bat while the Ball Tracking shows the wickets missing by a very small margin. Excellent review from Ravichandran Ashwin.

NOT OUT! Ravichandran Ashwin survives and this is a good review from Ashwin! This is a loopy ball, on a length, around middle. Ashwin tries to sweep but he misses and gets hit on his thigh pad. Sri Lanka appeal and the umpire agrees. Ashwin opts for a review and the Ball Tracker shows that the ball would have gone on to miss the stumps. Another successful review for India!
Flatter ball, around off. Ravichandran Ashwin skips down the track and looks to block but he misses and gets rapped on his pad.
Flatter ball, going on with the arm from middle. Shreyas Iyer tucks it towards square leg.
This is tossed up, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja gets down on his knee and paddles it through fine leg for a single. 150 comes up for India!
Floated, full and around off. Ashwin jams it out towards cover. Not in the gap though!
Tosses this one up, around off. Ashwin prods and pushes it towards cover.
This is flatter and on middle. Ashwin keeps it out watchfully.
Tossed up, around off. Ravichandran Ashwin blocks it off the front foot.
Praveen Jayawickrama (10-2-52-1) is back on.
Floated, on a length, outside off and spinning away late. Shreyas Iyer sways away from the line of the ball.
This is a flatter ball, on a length, around middle. Ravichandran Ashwin looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge behind square on the leg side for a run.
Ravichandran Ashwin comes in now.

OUT! CAUGHT! The hero of the previous match departs and Lasith Embuldeniya gets his third wicket! Another Indian batter tries to cut and ends up giving away his wicket. This is a flatter ball, turning in from outside off. Jadeja hangs back to cut but the ball takes off from a length and hits his glove. It pops out towards the slip fielder where Lahiru Thirimanne takes a simple catch.
Commentary.Howout: c Lahiru Thirimanne b Lasith Embuldeniya

Commentary.Commentary: Shorter in length, around off. Iyer rocks back and helps it on its way towards deep square leg for a run.
Flatter and quicker, around middle. Iyer dabs it onto the deck.
FOUR! Nicely played! This is tossed up, on middle. Iyer clears his front leg and whips it wide of the mid on fielder for a boundary.
Much slower through the air, around off. Ravindra Jadeja pushes it to the off side. A maiden over from Dhananjaya de Silva!
Tossed up, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja prods and drives it towards the extra cover fielder.
Floated, full and around off. Ravindra Jadeja keeps it out watchfully.
A loopy ball, around off. Ravindra Jadeja dead bats it.
Flatter and quicker, outside off and spinning away sharply. Jadeja leaves it alone in the end.
Tosses it up nicely, around middle. Jadeja blocks it out.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Shreyas Iyer keeps it out.
FOUR! Streaky! A loopy ball, outside off and spinning away. Shreyas Iyer prods and throws his bat at it. It goes off the outside edge, over the backward point fielder and into the fence.
FOUR BYES! TURN AND BOUNCE! This is tossed up, around off that turns away from the batter. Iyer looks to defend off the front foot but the ball beats his outside edge and goes past the keeper.
Floated, full and around off. Shreyas Iyer blocks it to the off side.
FOUR! Super shot from Iyer! Tossed up, around off. Iyer clears his front leg and carves it through the extra cover region for a boundary.
Tossed up, just outside off. Shreyas Iyer looks for a reverse sweep but he misses and gets hit on his pad.
Inside edge saves Jadeja! A flatter ball that goes on with the arm from middle. Ravindra Jadeja looks to defend but he gets an inside edge onto his pad.
Tossed up, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja defends it off the front foot.
A quicker ball, around middle. Ravindra Jadeja dabs it onto the deck.
Flatter and on off. Blocked out.
Flatter and quicker, going on with the arm, around middle. Ravindra Jadeja tries to pull but he misses and gets hit on his pad.
A full ball, around off. Shreyas Iyer prods and flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.

FOUR! Edgy but India will take it as they come now! Another ball, full and outside off. Jadeja prods to drive but it goes off the thick outside edge past the slip fielder and races away to thefence. Jadeja is underway!
Tosses it up, around off. Jadeja blocks it off the front foot.
The hero of the last match, Ravindra Jadeja walks out to the middle.

OUT! TIMBER! Lasith Embuldeniya strikes and he gets rid of the dangerous Pant! This is a flatter ball, outside off that spins in late. Rishabh Pant hangs back and looks to guide it past slip but it is too close to cut and the ball sneaks through his bat and pad to cannon onto his off stump. Huge moment in this game as Pant can run away with the game.
Commentary.Howout: b Lasith Embuldeniya

Commentary.Commentary: FOUR LEG BYES! This is a quicker ball, outside off. Rishabh Pant looks to defend off the front foot but he is a bit late. The ball ricochets off his pad and races away to the fence as the keeper does not grab it cleanly.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Rishabh Pant tries to cut but he gets an inside edge and onto the deck.
A short ball, around off. Rishabh Pant rocks back and cuts it wide of long off for a brace.
Lasith Embuldeniya is back into the attack.
A quicker ball, on off. Iyer hangs back to defend it.
Short and around off. Pant flat-bats it past the diving fielder at extra cover for a single.
Floated, on a length, well outside off. Rishabh Pant lets it be.
Full and on middle. Iyer works it to long on for a run.
Slower through the air, around middle. Iyer blocks it out.
Floated, full and outside off. Rishabh Pant drives it to deep cover for a single.
FOUR! CRUNCHED! Slightly shorter in length, around off. Shreyas Iyer rocks back and slaps it through the cover region for a boundary. 13 runs off the over!
A length ball, around leg. Rishabh Pant nudges it around the corner and takes a single.
FOUR! Another ball, turning into the pads. Pant hangs back and whips it behind square on the leg side. The fielder at deep square leg runs across to his left, puts in a dive but the ball wins.
Flatter and quicker, well outside off. Pant tries to cut it but he misses.
Tosses it up, well outside off. Rishabh Pant skips down the track and manages to block it out in the end.
FOUR! This is a flatter ball, around leg. Rishabh Pant stays back and tickles it through the fine leg region for another boundary. He is 30 off just 15 balls.
Around off. This is hit to point for one more. 11 coming off the over.
Tossed up, around off. Pant tries to reverse-sweep it but mistimes it completely.
FOUR! He plays without any pressure! A low full toss, around off. Pant caresses it through cover for a boundary.
FOUR! Good use of the feet! Tossed up, full and on middle. Pant skips down the track and tonks it well over mid on for a boundary.
Tossed up, on middle. Iyer flicks it through the diving mid-wicket fielder for a single.
Fuller ball, on off, pushed to long off for a single.
We are back for the middle session! The players have made their way out to the middle. Rishabh Pant and Shreyas Iyer will resume their innings. Dhananjaya de Silva will start with the ball. Let's go!
... Day 1, Session 2 ...

India did not get off to a great start as a mix-up between Rohit Sharma and Mayank Agarwal saw Agarwal heading back to the pavilion. Rohit Sharma did look good but the story was completely different once the spinners were introduced into the attack. Virat Kohli and Hanuma Vihari steadied the ship for a while after the skipper perished but a wicket was always around the corner. Both Kohli and Vihari were sent back just at the stroke of Tea and Rishabh Pant has come out with some intent. He will look to carry on his merry way as every run is going to be crucial on a track that is playing a lot of tricks. It will be interesting to see how the middle session pans out which begins at 4.20 pm IST (10.50 am GMT). Do join us then!

What a session we have witnessed and it is the tourists who would be happier going into the Tea break. The pitch has already started shaking hands with the spinners on Day 1 of this Test. There is a lot of assistance for the spinners on this track and the Lankan spinners have done a good job of sending back India's top order. Although, they were a bit inconsistent at the start but as the innings progressed, they seemed to have found the rhythm. A total of three spinners were used by Dimuth Karunaratne and they got one wicket apiece.

An appeal for LBW but nothing given! This is full and spinning around leg. Iyer goes back to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal but that was sliding down. No review taken as well and that will be Tea on Day 1.
Tossed up, full and outside off, spinning away. Iyer lunges to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Darted on the pads. Pant nudges it to deep square leg for one more.
Full and on middle, flicked to square leg for a single.
A full ball, turning sharply onto the pads. Pant whacks it to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Freebie! A full toss, on middle. Pant hammers it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Fuller ball, spinning into the right-hander. Iyer defends it out.
Stays low yet again! A loopy ball, landing on middle and spinning in late. Shreyas Iyer gets forward and looks to defend but it hits the toe end of his bat.
On middle, tucked to short leg.
Shreyas Iyer walks out to bat.

OUT! LBW! Virat Kohli is a goner and he can't do anything about this delivery. He just stands there and watches the pitch, that's all he can do. Dhananjaya de Silva gets the big fish in his very first over. A tossed up delivery, full and around off, the ball turns and literally dies after landing. Virat Kohli rocks back to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. That was plumb, really plumb. An appeal and up goes the finger. India in massive trouble here.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Dhananjaya de Silva

Commentary.Commentary: Tossed up, on off, driven to covers for a single.
Flatter and on off. Pant keeps it out.
Dhananjaya de Silva comes to bowl now. He replaces Lasith Embuldeniya.
Fuller and outside off, driven to covers for a single. An eventful over comes to an end.

FOUR! DROPPED! This is Pant, do-or-die each ball. Fuller and on middle. Pant comes down the track and goes big on the leg side. It goes of the toe end towards deep mid-wicket where Suranga Lakmal runs back and to his left but fails to catch it. The ball rolls behind to the fence. Was not that tough to take it though.
FOUR! Rather than building pressure, Praveen Jayawickrama gives a freebie here! A shorter ball, angling around off. Pant cuts it to point for a boundary and gets off the mark.
A loopy ball, on off. Pant defends it.
Rishabh Pant walks in at number 5.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Brilliant from Praveen Jayawickrama! He bowls it full and asks Hanuma Vihari to get forward to defend. The ball turns away after landing and takes the outside edge of his blade and goes to Niroshan Dickwella, behind the sticks who juggles a bit but holds onto it in the end. The 47-run partnership has been broken and Praveen Jayawickrama is rewarded with a wicket.
Commentary.Howout: c Niroshan Dickwella b Praveen Jayawickrama

Commentary.Commentary: Tossed up, on middle. Vihari gets an inside edge as he looks to defend, onto the pads.
Virat Kohli presses forward and defends this full ball back to the bowler.
Tossed up, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, fuller and angling around leg. Kohli looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. A stifled appeal follows.
Tossed up, on off. Kohli lunges and blocks it.
Fuller ball, outside off, pushed to covers. Lasith Embuldeniya overstepped and a no ball is called.
FOUR! Good shot! Shorter, slower in the air and outside off. Kohli has enough time to get into position as he cuts it through third man for a boundary.
Slightly short and outside off. Kohli punches off the back foot to cover.s
Lands outside off and spins more away. Easy leave.
Down the leg side, this is hit to short leg.
Shorter and outside off, cut away to point.
This is flatter and coming with the angle, the ball slides in and whizzes past the off pole. Hanuma prods and leaves it very late. That was very close.
On middle, eased to mid on.
Very full and going down, whipped to deep mid-wicket for a single.
A round arm delivery, around off. Vihari punches it to point.
A straight one, outside off. Left alone.
Darted on the pads, Kohli tickles it to deep square leg for one.
Flatter ball, outside off. Kohli presses forward and shoulders arms to it.
Full ball, on middle, drilled to mid on.
Short and outside off. Kohli slaps it hard and the ball hits the fielder at silly point.
Full, outside off. Left alone.

Review! Hanuma Vihari has reviewed it after being adjudged LBW! It looked like going down leg to the naked eye! The Ball tracker shows that the ball would have missed the leg stump. The on-field decision is overturned!

NOT OUT! Good review from Hanuma Vihari! An arm ball, flatter and around middle and leg. Hanuma Vihari gets on the back foot to flick it but misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal and up goes the finger. Vihari walks down towards Kohli and asks him whether to take it upstairs. Kohli suggests it was going down with the angle and the Ball Tracking shows the same, it is missing the stumps. India retain their review!
Angles a full ball, on middle and spinning away. Vihari keeps it out.
Slants a full ball, on middle. Vihari blocks it.
Tossed up, on off. Hanuma defends with an angled bat to point.
Full and on middle. Blocked out.
Flatter, sharp turn and bounce there. Kohli taps it late and to the right of gully. Both the spinners are getting great amount of turn but are not able to find that proper line and length.
Too full, on middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Flighted, full and on off. Kohli lunges and defends.
Short, outside off, width given. Kohli cuts it hard and to deep point for a brace.
Tossed up, on off. Kohli gets back and dead bats it.
Fuller and on off, pushed to covers.
Fuller and on off. Blocked out.
Again sharp spin. This time Vihari prods to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge,
This one lands on off and spins away sharply. Vihari first thinks to play at it but leaves it alone.
Around off. Blocked out.
Too full and on middle. Kohli whips it to deep mid-wicket and the fielder from square leg has to charge across, saves a single. Three runs taken.
Flatter and on off. Kohli punches it on the off side.
Flatter and quicker, around middle. Vihari gets back and wrists it towards the short leg fielder.
Tosses it up, around off. Vihari smothers the spin and keeps it out.
A short ball, outside off. Hanuma Vihari cuts but finds the backward point fielder.
Flighted ball, around leg. Hanuma Vihari defends it to the leg side.
That stayed low! Floated, on a length, around off and staying a touch low. Vihari stays back to defend but he gets an outside edge towards the point region.
Drop and run! Flatter ball, on a length, outside off. Virat Kohli rocks back and taps it in front of square on the off side for a single.
A loopy ball, well outside off. Hanuma Vihari does not go chasing for it.
Floated, on a length, outside off. Hanuma Vihari leaves it alone.
Flatter ball, on a length and going on with the arm. Vihari leans to defend but it goes off the thick inside edge, wide of the leg slip fielder.
Around off, blocked out.
FOUR! Clever shot from Vihari! This is a loopy ball, around middle. Vihari gets forward, takes it on the full and paddles it through the fine leg region for a boundary.
Tosses it up, around off. Vihari blocks it off the front foot.
Slightly shorter in length, around off. Kohli gets right back and defends it onto the deck.
Flatter and quicker, around middle. Virat Kohli stays back and works it wide of the mid on fielder for a brace.
FOUR! WHACKED! A Virat Kohli special! This is tossed up, outside off. Kohli gets forward and carves it through the cover region for a boundary. This might get him going now!
Flatter ball, on a length, around leg. Hanuma Vihari nudges it around the corner and takes a single.
Another ball that is way outside off. Hanuma Vihari stays back and does not offer any shot to that one.
A wayward ball, well outside off. Hanuma Vihari lets it be.
Tossed up, around off. Kohli keeps it out.
In the air but safe! Flatter ball, around middle. Kohli looks to flick and closes the bat face early. It takes the leading edge and falls just short of the cover fielder.
BEATEN! Excellent delivery! Slower through the air, on a length, around off and spinning away from the batter. Kohli looks to defend it off the front foot but the ball zips past his outside edge.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Goes back in his crease and defends it.
Floated, full and outside off. Kohli leaves it alone.
Tosses it up, around off. Virat Kohli gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks it.
This is a quicker ball that goes on with the arm, from middle. Kohli rocks back and tucks it to square leg for a quick single.
Slightly short and outside off. Hanuma Vihari taps it wide of point and takes a run.
Floated, full and around off. Hanuma Vihari keeps it out off the front foot.
Full and outside off. Hanuma Vihari lets it through to the keeper.
FOUR! Excellent timing and placement from Vihari! Slower through the air, full and outside off. Vihari prods and caresses it through the cover region for a boundary.
Flatter ball, outside off. Hanuma Vihari lets it be.
This is strayed on the pads. Kohli flicks it wide of deep mid-wicket and comes back for the second run.
BEATEN! This is tossed up, around middle. Kohli had to play at it. He gets forward to block but the ball spins past his blade. Lovely bowling!
Tossed up, around off. Virat Kohli stretches forward and keeps it out.
Flatter ball, going on with the angle from middle. Vihari flicks it to deep square leg for one run.
A yorker-length ball, on off. Hanuma Vihari digs it out.
FOUR! Nicely played! An overpitched ball, outside off. Hanuma Vihari clears his front leg and carves it past mid off for a boundary.
Floated, full and on off. Virat Kohli gets forward and blocks it.
Slightly shorter in length and outside off. Virat Kohli stays back to cut but he fails to get any bat on it.
Flatter and quicker, just outside off and spinning away late. Virat Kohli prods and lets it sail through.
Another loopy ball, full and outside off. Virat Kohli drives it to the man at extra cover.
Tosses it up, full and outside off. Kohli pushes it to cover.
Fulla and on off. Virat Kohli looks to drive but he gets an inside edge onto his pad.
A bit quicker, on a length, outside off. Hanuma Vihari lets it be.
A full ball, on middle. Virat Kohli flicks it through square leg and rotates the strike. Not a good start from Praveen Jayawickrama!
Dragged down, around leg. Hanuma Vihari rocks back and pulls it behind square on the leg side for a single this time.
Tosses it up, around leg. Hanuma Vihari kneels and paddles it through fine leg for a brace.
FOUR! SMASHED! A half-tracker, around off. Hanuma Vihari rocks back in his crease and pulls it in front of square for a boundary.
A full ball, down leg. Hanuma Vihari misses his flick.

Drinks! An opening hour dominated by the tourists. They have sent both the openers back and are bowling brilliantly. The pacers are bit erring with their lines while Lasith Embuldeniya since introduced is getting sharp turn and have already got the prized wicket of Rohit Sharma. Hanuma Vihari looks settled now and Virat Kohli will look to partner him in the middle. Also, Praveen Jayawickrama is into the attack now. Spin from both ends. A slip, gully and a short leg in place.
Slightly shorter in length, outside off. Virat Kohli stays back and taps it towards the point fielder.
An overpitched ball, around off. Hanuma Vihari drills it to the left of the bowler. Lasith Embuldeniya dives there and makes a half-stop. The batters cross ends.
Fuller in length, just outside off. Hanuma Vihari leaves it alone.
A loopy ball, on a length, around off. Hanuma Vihari hangs back and dabs it onto the deck.
Flatter and quicker, angling in from middle. Virat Kohli stays back and nudges it to the leg side for a run. Kohli is up and running!
Tosses it up, around off. Kohli gets forward and defends it with soft hands.
A yorker-length delivery, around middle. Hanuma Vihari squeezes it out towards mid on. Another maiden over from Lakmal!
Good-length delivery, around off. Hanuma Vihari prods and defends it to the off side.
Lakmal goes wide of the crease and serves a full-length ball, around off. Hanuma Vihari blocks it off the front foot.
Lakmal goes full and outside off. Hanuma Vihari lets it through to the keeper.
Chopped on, almost! Back of a length, jagging back in from off. Hanuma Vihari hangs back to defend but the ball hits the inside edge of the blade and falls just wide of the stumps.
A length ball, angling in from middle. Hanuma Vihari blocks it towards mid on.
Very full and on middle. Kohli solidly defends it.
This one stays low a bit but Kohli gets on his back foot to block it.
Fuller, outside off on a driving length. Kohli prods and leaves it alone.
The Bengaluru crowd erupts as Virat Kohli walks out to bat at number 4.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Sri Lanka get the second wicket and this has been a brilliant start for the visitors. Tossed up, fuller and outside off, turning sharply away. Rohit Sharma lunges to defend but gets an outside edge to second slip where Dhananjaya de Silva holds onto it. Good aggressive field placement from the skipper, Dimuth Karunaratne.
Commentary.Howout: c Dhananjaya de Silva b Lasith Embuldeniya

Commentary.Commentary: Slants a full ball, on middle. Vihari gets an inside edge on his attempted defense, to square leg for a single.
Tossed up, spinning outside off. Vihari plays it very late to point.
Good delivery! Angles a length ball, outside off and nips away off the deck. Rohit is squared up as he looks to defend and gets an outside edge well short of third slip.
Fuller and on middle. Sharma punches it straight down to the right of mid off.
Length ball, well outside off. Sharma shoulders arms.
Fullish and outside off, Rohit easily leaves it.
Slight halt in play. Suranga Lakmal seems to be having some issue with his neck and out comes the Sri Lankan physio. Lakmal seems fine now and we are good to go.
Length ball, outside off. Vihari drops it to the left of the bowler and calls for a single. Lakmal runs there, collects the ball and has a shy at his end but he misses. Vihari was well home though.
Length ball and Vihari keeps it out.

Fuller ball, angling around off and spins away off the deck. Vihari comes forward to defend but gets an outside edge to the right of first slip who dives but the ball goes past him for a single. Lasith Embuldeniya got turn in almost every ball.
Floated, full and around off. Blocked out.
Flatter and outside off, turning away. Vihari punches it to covers.
Drops it slightly short and outside off. Vihari cuts it past point for a brace.
Bit of turn, fuller and outside off. Vihari prods and defends.
Time for some spin as Lasith Embuldeniya comes into the attack now.
Tossed up, full and on off. Vihari defends on the front foot.
Length and on off, the ball holds in the deck a bit. Rohit strides to defend it late.
Touch fuller, slanting around the 4th stump channel. Sharma gets low to keep it out.
Length ball, outside off. Sharma presses forward and defends it out.
Fuller and outside off. Rohit defends it.
Length ball, outside off. Vihari defends it away from the body and gets an inside edge to deep square leg. A single taken.
A length ball, swinging a hint away. Vihari shoulders arms to it.
SIX! Bengaluru erupts! Short of a length, on middle. Rohit Sharma pulls it all the way over square leg for a biggie. First of the match.
Length ball, on off. Sharma defends with a straight bat.
Anything on the pads and Rohit making the most of it. Again angles it on the pads. Rohit tickles it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Length ball, spilled way down the leg side. Sharma leaves it.
On a length, on off. Sharma on his toes, blocks it out.
Slants a full ball, but spills it way outside off. Rohit lets it through.
A length ball, outside off. Vihari offers no shot. Maiden by Lakmal.
Full, well wide outside off. Left alone.
A length ball, outside off and nipping back sharply. Vihari shoulders arms to it and Niroshan Dickwella takes it to his left.
This one comes with the angle and goes just over the off pole. Vihari with another leave.
A length ball, seaming outside off and shaping away late. Vihari shoulders arms.
Shorter and outside off. Vihari leaves it alone.
Length ball, around middle. Rohit nudges it to deep square leg for another brace.
Leg bye! A length ball, tailing on the pads. Vihari misses his flick. It goes off the pads and to fine leg.
Length, outside off. Left alone.
Slightly back of a length, on middle. Hanuma on the back foot, looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
A length ball, angling across, and shapes away off the deck. Vihari defends inside the line and misses.
A fuller ball, on middle. Vihari flicks it through mid-wicket and gets off the mark with a couple of runs.
Short of a length, outside off, hint of away shape as well. Sharma flashes at it but misses.
Length ball, outside off. Sharma defends with soft hands on the deck.
Fuller ball, outside off, does not bounce much. Rohit shoulders arms to it.
Length and outside off. Rohit drops it to point.
A length ball, outside off. Rohit guides it to point where a fumble happens but Rohit is not taking a single.
BEATEN! Lakmal serves a length ball, just outside off and nips away slightly. Rohit Sharma tries to defend off the front foot but the ball zips past his outside edge.
This is a length ball, just outside off. Hanuma Vihari prods and blocks it towards cover.
Back of a length, around off. Hanuma Vihari hangs back and taps it to the off side.
A length ball, around off. Vihari keeps it out.
Hanuma Vihari walks out to bat.

OUT! RUN OUT! What is happening here? Absolute chaos in the middle and India lose their opener in the process. A length ball, swinging in from middle. Agarwal misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. A huge, huge appeal for LBW but nothing given. The ball drops to point and Agarwal keeps his head down and runs across. Meanwhile, Rohit is ball watching and there is an easy run out at the keeper's end. The umpire signals a no ball and that would be not out in case it was given LBW but Agarwal is clearly run out as Praveen Jayawickrama at point throws the ball to Niroshan Dickwella who collects the ball and whips the bails off. A bizarre way to get out. Sri Lanka strike early.
Commentary.Howout: run out (Praveen Jayawickrama / Niroshan Dickwella)

Commentary.Commentary: Length ball, on the hips, tucked to deep square leg for one.
Length ball, straight around off. Rohit prods and defends it out.
FOUR! Sharma is off the mark as well. A length ball, swinging onto the pads. Sharma flicks it well wide of deep square leg for a boundary.
Vishwa Fernando to operate from the other end.
Length ball, just outside off. Mayank Agarwal has his stumps covered as he makes another leave.
Fuller again, outside off, and moving away. Mayank lets it be.
FOUR! India and Mayank Agarwal are underway! This is too full from Lakmal, outside off. Agarwal leans and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Length and on off. Mayank blocks it out.
Good line! A length ball, angling on middle, it lands and nips away. Agarwal looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads
Lakmal starts with a length ball, outside off and shaping away sharply. Agarwal leaves it alone.

We are set for the game to begin! The Sri Lankan players give a guard of honor to Suranga Lakmal who is playing his last Test match. The players then take their respective fielding positions. Mayank Agarwal and Rohit Sharma to open the batting for India. Agarwal is on strike. Suranga Lakmal will start proceedings with the ball. Here we go...

Dimuth Karunaratne, the skipper of Sri Lanka, says the wicket is very dry and it will turn later on, so they wanted to bat first as well. Adds that they talked about the last match and will make sure that the mistakes don't happen again. Informs there are two changes to their side.

Rohit Sharma, the skipper of India, says that they will bat first. Adds that it looks like a dry pitch and they have made one change to their side. Tells that they added one more spinner as the pitch is very dry. Says that it is unfortunate that Jayant Yadav has to miss out but Axar Patel has done well for them in the past. Says that they want to be ruthless as a unit.

Sri Lanka (Playing XI) - Dimuth Karunaratne (C), Lahiru Thirimanne, Kusal Mendis (In for Pathum Nissanka), Angelo Mathews, Dhananjaya de Silva, Charith Asalanka, Niroshan Dickwella (WK), Suranga Lakmal, Lasith Embuldeniya, Vishwa Fernando, Praveen Jayawickrama (In for Lahiru Kumara).

India (Playing XI) - Rohit Sharma (C), Mayank Agarwal, Hanuma Vihari, Virat Kohli, Shreyas Iyer, Rishabh Pant (WK), Ravindra Jadeja, Ravichandran Ashwin, Axar Patel (In for Jayant Yadav), Mohammed Shami, Jasprit Bumrah.
TOSS - Up goes the coin and it lands in favor of Rohit Sharma. India will BAT first!

PITCH REPORT - Deep Dasgupta and Russel Arnold are near the pitch. The former says that the spinners will play a key factor as the pitch looks dry and the captain winning the toss will look to bat first. Adds, the sun is beating down and the cracks will open up, with turn and bounce, spinners will enjoy it. Tells, it will be a challenge to play the spinners and the batters should be careful.

Coming into this pink-ball Test, we might see both sides make some changes to their lineups and Sri Lanka have already named a few of those. Pathum Nissanka and Dushmantha Chameera are two forced changes and we expect more by Sri Lanka. Both India and Sri Lanka will need their batters to put their best foot forward against the pink ball which does a lot more in the air and off the surface than the red cherry. Lots of things to look forward to in the second and the final Test of the series which promises to be a cracker with 100% crowd allowed in the stadium. Stay tuned for toss and further updates.

Hello and a very warm welcome to the coverage of this pink-ball Test match between India and Sri Lanka at the iconic M. Chinnaswamy Stadium in Bengaluru. India won the first Test quite comprehensively and they will be keen to whitewash the Lankans who will be under the pump heading into this Test. It is a do-or-die encounter for Sri Lanka and Dimuth Karunaratne and his troops would be eager to stage a comeback and show some resistance against a strong Indian side.
... Day 1, Session 1...
We are back for India's second innings. The players walk out to the middle. Rohit Sharma and Mayank Agarwal are the openers. Suranga Lakmal has the ball...Two slips and a gully in place.
... Third innings ...

The Indian attack was always going to be hard to face on this kind of track and they have been absolutely sensational right from the word go. It was Mohammed Shami and Jasprit Bumrah who struck in the last session on Day 1 and the spinners also backed it up by bowling tight lines and lengths. On a track which is turning square, the Indian pacers have taken seven wickets between them and that tells us the quality of both - India's bowling and Sri Lanka's batting. It was Ravichandran Ashwin and Jasprit Bumrah who picked up two wickets apiece in the first session of Day 2 and that ended Sri Lanka's misery. India now have a very healthy lead and their batters will look to pile on more runs and set a huge target in front of the tourists.

Sri Lanka have been bundled out cheaply for 109 and this is Sri Lanka's second-lowest total in Test cricket against India. This has been another dismal batting performance from the tourists and apart from Angelo Mathews and Niroshan Dickwella, no other batter managed to put on some kind of fight. They have been well below-par with the bat and the Lankans never really looked like scoring big against a strong Indian attack. India get a first innings lead of 143 runs.

OUT! STUMPING! This was very slow, carrom ball and way outside off. Fernando is deceived by the pace and misses his push. Pant collects it and removes the bails. The replay shows Fernando had his back foot in the air while the bails were removed and that will be the end of Sri Lanka's inning. Sri Lanka trail by 143 runs.
Commentary.Howout: st Rishabh Pant b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary.Commentary: Stumping-check! Rishabh Pant has disturbed the stumps and Vishwa Fernando might be in trouble here. The replays roll in and it shows that Fernando had his back foot in the air. India get their last wicket.
FOUR! Slower through the air, full and on off. Fernando goes downtown, over mid off for a boundary.
Tossed up, on off. Fernando slog-sweeps it. Hits it high and wide of long on for another couple. Just over Axar Patel there.
Fuller ball, outside off. Fernando mistimes his sweep through square leg and takes a couple of runs.
Fuller ball, outside off, pushed to covers for a single.
A slower ball, at 125 clicks, around off. Fernando defends it to covers.
A yorker, it was always coming from Bumrah but Fernando does well to dig it out.
Length ball, outside off. Fernando tries to chase this one and misses.
Short and on middle. Vishwa ducks under it.
Vishwa Fernando is the last batter in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Five-fer for Jasprit Bumrah! Bangs a bouncer, on middle. Not quite sure if Niroshan Dickwella tries to play the ramp shot or bend his back and leave it alone. The ball stays a bit low off the deck and takes his gloves on its way to the keeper, Pant who appeals and the umpire already had his finger up. What a performance this has been from Jasprit Bumrah! His first five-wicket haul in India!
Commentary.Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary.Commentary: Fuller ball, around off. Dickwella works it to point.
Praveen Jayawickrama walks out to bat.

OUT! TIMBER! That was special from Ashwin. This one is a carrom ball, fuller and on middle, it lands and spins away. Lakmal again looks to play it across the line but gets beaten on the outside edge and the ball hits the stumps. Sri Lanka still trail by 152 runs.
Commentary.Howout: b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary.Commentary: FOUR! Wide of the fielder! Tossed up, on middle. Lakmal heaves it and hits it well wide of long on for a boundary. 100 up for the Lankans.
Comes around the wicket, fuller and on middle. Blocked out on the front foot.
Floated, full and on off. Lakmal prods and defends.
This one lands outside off and spins in. Lakmal has his bat down to defend.
Tossed up, on off. Lakmal is behind the line to block it.

Superb work from Pant! Fuller and on the pads. Dickwella flicks it late and to the right of the keeper. Pant puts a dive and stops the ball from running away. Dickwella does not take the run. Lakmal to face the next over, just what India wanted.
Very full, outside off, pushed to covers for Lakmal to get off the mark.
On a length, on off, this one nips in late. Lakmal looks to defend and does so off the inner half of his blade.
Short of a length, sliding on middle. Lakmal sits under it.
Who will bat now?

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Bumrah continues from where he left off. Bumrah steams in and serves a pacy short ball, on middle. Embuldeniya tries to ride the bounce as he looks to pull but gets a top edge, in the air, behind the sticks for Pant to gobble it up. Easy work for the keeper. Sri Lanka 7 down now.
Commentary.Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary.Commentary: A length ball, just outside off. Embuldeniya keeps it out on the off side.
Darted on the pads, flicked to square leg for a quick single.
On middle. Defended out.

NOT OUT! This is tossed up, it lands on off and spins away sharply. Embuldeniya takes a big stride forward and is beaten by the spin as he looks to defend. Pant, behind the stumps, removes the bails in flash. The replay shows Embuldeniya has his back foot planted.

Stumping-check! Rishabh Pant has whipped the bails off as Lasith Embuldeniya stretches forward to block. He has missed it and Embuldeniya might be in trouble. The replays roll in and it shows that Embuldeniya had his back foot grounded inside the crease. NOT OUT!
Full and around off. Embuldeniya strides forward to defend it out.
Tossed up, on middle. Lasith Embuldeniya leans and blocks it.
A flatter ball, angling around off. Lasith Embuldeniya blocks it on the off side.
Ravichandran Ashwin will operate from the other end.
Length ball, outside off. Dickwella leaves it alone. Good comeback from Bumrah after going for boundaries.
Pitches it up, around off, pushed to mid off.
Length ball, way outside off. Dickwella flashes at it but misses.
Fuller this time, on middle. Blocked on the deck.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! A length ball, coming with the angle! Dickwella stays back and punches it through gully for another boundary.
FOUR! A wonderful start for Sri Lanka! Bumrah starts from around the wicket. On a length and outside off. Dickwella punches it softly and through gully for a boundary.

We are set for Day 2 to get underway! The Indian players have made their way out to the middle. The overnight batters, Niroshan Dickwella and Lasith Embuldeniya are at the crease. A slight halt in play as a swarm of bees has entered the stadium. Looks like the swarm has gone away and we are good to go. Jasprit Bumrah will start proceedings with the ball. Let's go...

PITCH REPORT - Deep Dasgupta and Ajit Agarkar are near the pitch. They say Sri Lanka got turn and invariable bounce in the first session on Day 1 and expect the same on Day 2 as well. Adds that there was more movement under the lights for the pacers. Tells that the spinners will enjoy the conditions again.

Rishabh Pant is up for a quick chat. He says that the pitch didn't turn much in the last two sessions on Day 1. Adds that the wicket was on the slower side but it got better to bat on as the game progressed. Tells that the pink ball moved a lot in the last session and they bowled well. Mentions, he tried to keep it simple and played the ball on it's merit when he went out to bat.

Sri Lanka do not have much batting left as Niroshan Dickwella is their last recognized batter in and they would hope that he bats deep and they get as close to India's total as possible. India on the other hand, will come out all guns blazing and they'll be keen to wrap things up quickly and get healthy first innings lead. Lot's to look forward to in the first session of Day 2 and we hope that it turns out to be an exciting one. Stay tuned for further updates.

Hello and a very warm welcome to the coverage of Day 2 of the pink-ball Test match between India and Sri Lanka. The hosts dominated Day 1 and Sri Lanka found themselves in a spot of bother yet again with the bat. They did bowl well in patches but leaked a lot of runs once Shreyas Iyer got his eye in. The Lankans lost six wickets in the final session and are trailing by 166 runs.
...Day 2, Session 1...

Right then! India bossed the first day of this pink-ball Test match and we expect the same on Day 2 as well. They would look to take the remaining 4 wickets quickly and get healthy first innings lead. Day 2 will start at 2 pm IST (8.30 am GMT). But as usual, the build-up will begin much earlier. Do join us then. Till then, Adios.

Shreyas Iyer is up for a quick chat. He says that there was a lot of drama happening in every over when he was watching the game before going in to bat and he said to himself that he will be looking to play his shots. Adds that he didn't want to get out defending the ball and when he was around 80, he started thinking about his hundred. On being asked about missing out on a hundred, he mentions that he has no regrets and is happy to contribute to the team's cause. Says that they knew the role of the fast bowlers would be very crucial in the last session and they did really well.

Earlier in the day, Sri Lankan bowlers didn't make the most of the pitch. Their spinners took wickets but gifted too many freebies as well which saw Shreyas Iyer take the game from 94/4 to 252. One of the finest knocks on a very tricky pitch.

A total of 16 wickets fell on the first day, highest ever in a pink-ball Test match. The spinners bossed for Sri Lanka but India were rewarded wickets by their front-line pacers. Both Bumrah and Shami were breathing fire early on and they piled the pressure. Sri Lankan batters were finding it so hard to face them. Bumrah took three wickets while Shami ended with a brace. Axar Patel got a solitary wicket as well.

India ended the first day on a high. They have managed to take six wickets and still lead by 166 runs. A superb bowling display from India. The ball got old and even the spinners were not getting much assistance but Bumrah managed to get the wicket of Angelo Mathews who was looking so good. Lasith Embuldeniya was LBW but India didn't take the review. A bit gutted but still, the hosts will be the happier side at the end of the day.
This is a length ball, around middle. Lasith Embuldeniya stays back and keeps it out on the leg side. That will be Stumps on Day 1!
Shami goes for a yorker, just outside off. Lasith Embuldeniya fails to dig it out.
A short ball, around middle. Lasith Embuldeniya takes his eyes off the ball and ducks under it.
Short of a length, outside off. Niroshan Dickwella hangs back and punches it to deep cover for a single.
Pitches it up, outside off. Niroshan Dickwella prods and pushes it towards cover.
Back of a length, around middle. Niroshan Dickwella hangs back and tucks it towards the leg gully fielder with soft hands.
Final over coming up and it will be Shami who will close the day.
A full ball, angling down leg. Lasith Embuldeniya misses his flick and Rishabh Pant behind the sticks, does well to grab it by diving to his right.

An appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved! Bumrah hurls a loopy full toss, around leg. Lasith Embuldeniya misses his flick and gets hit on his pad. Rohit Sharma doesn't opt for a review this time around.
Back of a length, around off at 143.3 clicks. Lasith Embuldeniya stays back to defend but he misses and gets hit high on his pad.
Another short ball, angling down leg. Lasith Embuldeniya lets it through to the keeper.
Bumrah comes 'round the wicket and serves a well-directed bumper, around off. Lasith Embuldeniya keeps it out awkwardly.
Lasith Embuldeniya walks out. Three slips, a silly point and a short leg.

OUT! CAUGHT! Oh, dear! Mathews played so well for his 43 but throws away his wicket just at the stroke of Stumps on Day 1. Bumrah serves an off-cutter, on a length, outside off. Angelo Mathews hangs back and looks to guide it over the slip cordon. He pokes at it and it goes off the outside edge towards Rohit Sharma at second slip who takes a sharp catch. End of a gritty innings from Mathews.
Commentary.Howout: c Rohit Sharma b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary.Commentary: Floated, full and on off. Niroshan Dickwella blocks it off the front foot.
Excellent delivery! Slower through the air, on a length, around off and spinning away late. Niroshan Dickwella prods to defend but the ball beats his outside edge.
Flatter ball, well outside off. Niroshan Dickwella slaps it through cover-point and takes a couple of runs.
This is darted on the pads. Angelo Mathews flicks it to the leg side and takes a single.
Floated full and spinning in from middle. Angelo Mathews misses his nudge on the leg side and gets hit high on his pad.
Ashwin tosses it up nicely, around off. Angelo Mathews tucks it to mid-wicket.
A length ball, jagging back in from middle. Angelo Mathews nudges it behind square on the leg side and retains the strike by taking a run.
A short ball, angling in from middle. Angelo Mathews ducks underneath.
That deceives Angelo Mathews completely! A slower ball, on a length, outside off. Angelo Mathews stays back to cut but he misses and the ball sneaks through his bat and goes to the keeper.
This is on a length, just outside off. Angelo Mathews tries to block it off the front foot but it goes off the outside edge past the backward point fielder for a brace.
Back of a length, well outside off. Angelo Mathews hangs back and taps it towards backward point.
Pitches it up, around off. Angelo Mathews defends it off the front foot.
Jasprit Bumrah is back into the attack.
Another ball that stays low! A loopy ball, on a length, around off and spinning away late. Niroshan Dickwella sits back to block but he misses as the ball goes past his blade.
Floated, full and outside off. Angelo Mathews sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
BEATEN! Flatter ball, on a length, outside off. Angelo Mathews stays back to block but the ball goes past his outside edge.

NOT OUT! A flatter ball, on middle. Niroshan Dickwella kneels to sweep but he gets an inside edge onto his pad. The ball rolls to the leg side and the batters look for a run. Virat Kohli runs towards the ball and scores a direct hit at the striker's end. However, Rishabh Pant had already disturbed the stumps with his gloves before the ball hit the stump and it is NOT OUT.
A run out appeal! The bails have lit up even before the ball hits as Rishabh Pant's finger touches the bails. Mathews is in before the direct hit comes. Not out it is.
Turn and bounce for Ashwin! This is tossed up, just outside off and spinning away from the batter. Niroshan Dickwella prods to defend but the ball beats his outside edge.
Tosses it up, around off. Niroshan Dickwella defends it off the front foot.
Full ball, slanting outside off. Mathews works it on the off side.
Angles a length ball, on the pads. Mathews clips it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Around off. Defended out.
FOUR! Good shot! Fuller ball, on off. Mathews goes inside-out over covers for a boundary. Really good shot this.
Shorter and on off. Punched off the back foot to covers.
A round arm delivery, on middle. Mathews blocks it.
On the pads, nudged to mid-wicket.
A low full toss, on middle, drilled to long on for one.
Full and on off, pushed to covers.
Flatter ball, around off, and spinning sharply into the right-hander. Mathews rocks back and keeps it out.
Fuller again, swept to deep square leg for a single.
Fuller ball, on middle. Dickwella blocks it out.
Slides a fuller ball, angling around off. Mathews defends it awkwardly.
Bangs a length ball, on off, it shoots off the deck and Mathews defends on the up.
SIX! Tossed up, angling on off. Mathews leans and hammers it over long off for a biggie.
Superb bowling! An arm ball, it lands on off and spins past the stumps. It was inches away from meeting the stumps.
Fuller ball, on middle. Blocked out.
Flatter, on a length, outside off, and spinning back in. Dickwella punches it to covers for a single.
Change of ends for Axar Patel.
Ashwin keeps bowling at a fuller-length and Dickwella this time sweeps it to fine leg for a single.
Another solid defense from Niroshan Dickwella.
Flighted in the air, on middle. Dickwella gets on the front foot to defend it out.
FOUR! A low full toss, on middle. Dickwella gets low and sweeps it to deep square leg for a boundary.
Flighted ball, on the pads, tucked to mid-wicket.
Floated, on middle. Dickwella presses to defend.
Ravichandran Ashwin (2-1-4-0) is back on.
Angles this one across, around off. Dickwella pushes it through covers for a single.
Full, slower in the air and on middle. Dickwella comes down and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, on middle. Mathews drills it wide of mid on for a single.
An arm ball, on middle, it straightens off the deck. Mathews gets low to defend it.
Tossed up, on middle. Mathews lunges and defends.
Fuller and outside off, turning away. Mathews looks to go big but mistimes it well over covers for a couple of runs.
On a length, around middle. Angelo Mathews tucks it to the leg side for a single.
Chopped on, almost! A quicker ball, on a length, around off. Angelo Mathews stays back to cut but gets an inside edge which falls just wide of the stumps.
Bye! A flatter ball, down leg. Niroshan Dickwella misses his flick and Rishabh Pant fails to gather it. The batters sneak in a bye.
Floated, full and around off. Niroshan Dickwella blocks it out.
Tossed up, around off. Niroshan Dickwella defends it off the front foot.
Fuller in length, on middle. Niroshan Dickwella pushes it towards mid on.
TURN AND BOUNCE! How do you play that one? This is a flatter ball, drifting in from off and turning away sharply. Angelo Mathews hangs back to defend but the ball beats his outside edge.
Floated, full and around middle. Angelo Mathews prods to defend it out.
Tossed up, around off. Angelo Mathews keeps it out.

Is that dropped? This is a flatter ball, outside off that spins in late. Niroshan Dickwella looks to tuck it on the leg side but he gets a thick inside edge and Rishabh Pant behind the sticks does not gather it cleanly. The batters cross ends.
Fuller in length, around off. Niroshan Dickwella keeps it out.
Tossed up, on middle. Niroshan Dickwella skips down the track and eases it to mid on.
Tossed up delivery, around off. Angelo Mathews stretches forward and blocks it.
Flatter ball, going on with the arm from off. Angelo Mathews blocks it off the front foot.
Flatter ball, on a length, around off. Angelo Mathews stays back and taps it to point.
Niroshan Dickwella is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Charith Asalanka looks to take Axar Patel on but he holes out! Sri Lanka slip further! Patel tosses it up, around off. Asalanka skips down the track and looks to go downtown. He miscues it high in the air, only towards mid off. Ravichandran Ashwin there, settles under it and pouches it with ease. Sri Lanka lose their fifth wicket now and are in some serious trouble.
Commentary.Howout: c Ravichandran Ashwin b Axar Patel

Commentary.Commentary: Much slower through the air, full and outside off. Charith Asalanka gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks it.
Tossed up, well outside off. Charith Asalanka kneels and reverse-sweeps it towards Jasprit Bumrah at backward point.
On a length, outside off. Angelo Mathews taps it towards point.
BEATEN! That turned square! Floated, on a length, around off and spinning away from the batter. Angelo Mathews gets forward to defend but the ball beats his outside edge.
Floated, full and outside off. Angelo Mathews blocks it.
Quicker through the air, on a length, around off. Angelo Mathews defends it onto the deck.
A full ball, on off. Angelo Mathews pushes it back to the bowler.
An overpitched ball, around off. Angelo Mathews squeezes it out.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Charith Asalanka keeps it out.
Tosses it up, on off. Mathews looks to block but it goes off the thick outside edge towards short third man for a single.
SIX! BANG! This is tossed up, on middle. Angelo Mathews prods and whacks it way over long off for a maximum.

In the air but safe! A flatter ball, on a length, around off that takes off from a length. Mathews looks to defend off the front foot but it hits the shoulder of his bat and pops out towards backward point.
Tossed up, on off. Angelo Mathews blocks it off the front foot.
An overpitched ball, around off. Angelo Mathews digs it out to mid on.

DRINKS! India are all over Sri Lanka at the moment and the tourists badly need a big partnership to stage a comeback in this contest. Angelo Mathews has done well so far to see off the new ball but he must now ensure that he bats deep and the Lankans do not lose any more wickets in the final session of Day 1. Axar Patel comes into the attack.
Slanting around off. Mathews punches it to covers for a quick single.
On middle. Defended out.
Quicker one, on middle. Angelo gets his bat down in time to defend.
Full ball, outside off, turning away. Left alone.
Another single as this is worked to mid on.
FOUR! A fuller ball, sliding around off. Asalanka comes down and chips it past mid-wicket, wide of long on for a boundary.
Touch fuller and on off. Angelo comes down as he keeps this out.
FOUR! Fuller ball, outside off. Mathews throws his bat at it, gets a thick outside edge to deep backward point for a boundary.
Length, outside off. Blocked out.
Length ball, outside off. Mathews guides it to point.
FOUR! Good shot! Fuller and on middle. Mathews drives it gently, straight down the ground for a boundary.
Bangs a short ball, on leg. Mathews ducks under it.
Jadeja changes the angle, around the wicket. This is full and spinning on middle. Asalanka keeps it out.
An arm ball, on middle, whipped to mid-wicket for a single.
Floated, full and on off. Defended out.
Full and on off, pushed to covers this time.
A quicker one at 94 clicks, angling on leg. Mathews prods and defends it out.
Tossed up, full and angling on middle. Blocked out.
Length ball, outside off. Asalanka leaves it alone.
Charith Asalanka walks out to bat.
Review! Rohit Sharma opts for another review as Dhananjaya de Silva has been struck on his pad. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it indicates three reds.

OUT! LBW! Sri Lanka in a big spot of bother here. A length ball, around off, it lands and jags back in sharply. de Silva again on the back foot, looks to flick it but misses and gets hit on the pads. The ball moved too much so Pant and Shami convinced Rohit Sharma to take it upstairs. UltraEdge shows no bat there. Ball Tracking shows wickets hitting. A wonderful review from India and they get the fourth wicket now. Shami gets his second.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Mohammed Shami

Commentary.Commentary: Touch fuller, around middle. de Silva on the back foot, tucks it to square leg.
Length ball, slanting on middle. Blocked out.
FOUR! A length ball, outside off. de Silva opens the face of the bat and guides it past point for a boundary.
Full and on middle. Mathews pushes off the inner half to mid-wicket where a misfield allows a single.
This is short and wide outside off. de Silva plays it late and past backward point for a couple of runs.
Around off. de Silva defends it out.
Tossed up, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva looks to push but the ball beats the outside edge.
Tossed up, on off. Mathews drops it to point and takes a quick single.
Shorter and on middle, it lands and spins away sharply, steep bounce as well. Mathews lets it through.
Fuller ball, outside off. Mathews drives it hard and to covers where Vihari does well to stop it.
Ravindra Jadeja is into the attack.
Shami goes full and well outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva prods but does not bother playing at that one. A maiden over from Shami!
A full ball, around off. Dhananjaya de Silva gets forward and blocks it.
Shorter in length, on middle. Dhananjaya de Silva defends it onto the deck.

A stifled appeal but turned down by the umpire. Back of a length, angling in from outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva stays back and looks to defend but he misses and gets hit high on his pad. Might have gone down leg.
This is full and outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva lets it sail through to the keeper.
Good-length ball, around off. Dhananjaya de Silva keeps it out.
Another ball, full and this time the line if well outside off. Mathews prods and drives it through cover-point for a couple of runs.
Fuller in length, angling in from middle. Angelo Mathews turns it to mid-wicket. Not in the gap though.
BEATEN ALL ENDS UP! A length ball, outside off that straightens a bit after landing. Angelo Mathews looks to defend off the back foot but he misses as the ball stays a touch low.
This is a full ball, outside off. Angelo Mathews throws his bat at it but it hits the toe end of his bat and goes towards the slip cordon.
Good-length delivery, around off. Angelo Mathews defends it to the off side.
The physio runs in but Angelo Mathews is good to go after getting hit on the shoulders.
Bumrah bends his back and hits the deck hard, around off. Angelo Mathews stays back to keep it out but he misses and gets hit high on his shoulder.
Pitches it up, around off. Dhananjaya de Silva looks to drive but it goes off the inner half of the bat past the mid-wicket fielder for a brace.
On a length, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva stays back to defend but it goes off the outer half of the blade towards point.
Good-length ball, around off. Dhananjaya de Silva sits back and defends it solidly.
Back of a length, around off. Dhananjaya de Silva gets on top of the bounce and blocks it.
Pitches it up, outside off and that ball nips back in late. Dhananjaya de Silva leaves it alone and the ball goes just past the off pole.
BEATEN! Shami runs in and serves a good-length ball, just outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva prods to defend but the ball jags away a bit and beats his outside edge.
Fuller in length, around middle. Angelo Mathews pushes it towards mid on. Another maiden over from Bumrah!
A length ball, nipping back in from off. Angelo Mathews gets forward and blocks it.
Hits the bat hard! Short of a length, angling in from outside off. Angelo Mathews stays back and defends it to the off side.
Back of a length, around middle. Angelo Mathews rides the bounce nicely and defends it onto the surface.
On a length, around off. Angelo Mathews dabs it onto the deck.

Edged but it falls short of the keeper! A length ball, around the corridor of uncertainty. Angelo Mathews hangs back to block but he gets an outside edge which lands just in front of Rishabh Pant behind the sticks.
On a length, around off. Dhananjaya de Silva keeps it out watchfully.
A length ball, jagging back in from middle. Dhananjaya de Silva nudges it around the corner and comes back for the second run. Dhananjaya de Silva is off the mark.
On a length, around middle. Dhananjaya de Silva blocks it off the back foot.
A length ball, down leg. Dhananjaya de Silva leaves it alone.
Review! Rohit Sharma wasn't at all convinced but he still goes upstairs. It clearly came off the bat. Not out it is.

NOT OUT! A big inside edge saves Dhananjaya de Silva! Good-length ball, around off. Dhananjaya de Silva stays back to block but he gets an inside edge onto his pad. Rohit Sharma opts for a review in the end after consulting with his teammates. Normal replay was enough for the third umpire to make a decision.
Dhananjaya de Silva comes in.
Mohammed Shami is into the attack.

OUT! BOWLED! What a peach of delivery first up from Shami! He comes 'round the wicket and serves a length ball, just outside off that jags back in late. Dimuth Karunaratne prods to block it but he misses it completely as the ball sneaks through the gap between his bat and pad. The ball crashes onto the off stump and the Bengaluru crowd erupts yet again. Sri Lanka are in a spot of bother once again.
Commentary.Howout: b Mohammed Shami

Commentary.Commentary: Length ball, shaping back in late. Mathews leaves it alone.
Fuller ball, angling on off. Defended out.
Angling on the pads, flicked to square leg.
Fuller and down the leg side. Angelo misses his flick.
Short of a length, around off. Angelo Mathews hops and blocks it.
Angelo Mathews walks out to bat.

OUT! TAKEN! Bumrah, edged, Iyer with the catch. Just like the previous wicket and India making early inroads. Bumrah changes the angle and comes 'round the wicket. This is a good-length ball and just outside off, around the fifth stump channel. Lahiru Thirimanne looks to push but the ball just jags away a bit and takes the outside edge to third slip where Shreyas Iyer takes his second catch. Not the most cleanest of catches but he does well to hold on to it.
Commentary.Howout: c Shreyas Iyer b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary.Commentary: FOUR! Sri Lanka playing with some intent! An arm ball, sliding on middle. Karunaratne bunts it through square leg for a boundary.
Fullish and on off, pushed to mid off.
Fuller and on middle. Karunaratne prods and defends.
Drifting well down on the pads. Karunaratne gets hit on the pads as he looks to defend. A stifled appeal follows.
Flatter, slower through the air, on middle. Blocked out.
Fuller and sliding on leg. Karunaratne whips it to short fine leg.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
FOUR! Two in a row! Bumrah struggling slightly here! On the hips this time. Lahiru Thirimanne flicks it off the back foot and wide of square leg for another boundary.
FOUR! First boundary off the innings! This is straight on the pads. Lahiru Thirimanne with a nice flick past mid-wicket for a boundary.
This one moves away from the left-hander, fuller and around middle. Lahiru Thirimanne is slightly squared up as he defends this one.
A half-hearted appeal for LBW turned down! A fuller ball, angling on the pads. Lahiru Thirimanne misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.
Lahiru Thirimanne walks in at number 3.

OUT! TAKEN! Sri Lanka lose a wicket early on! Bumrah steams in and serves it on a fullish length, outside off, Mendis looks to drive, without any foot movement and gets a thick outside edge to Shreyas Iyer at gully who dives low to his right and takes it.
Commentary.Howout: c Shreyas Iyer b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary.Commentary: Maiden to start by Ashwin! Tossed up, fuller and around off. Karunaratne presses forward to keep it out.
This one comes with the arm, on middle. Karunaratne lunges to defend.
Floated, full and around off. Karunaratne defends it on the off side.
Tossed up, on off. Karunaratne blocks it out.
Fuller ball, outside off. Karunaratne prods and defends.
A flatter ball, skidding on the pads. Dimuth Karunaratne misses his flick. Only Kohli at slips appeals for it.
Ravichandran Ashwin will bowl from the other end.
What a peach of a delivery! Bumrah hurls in and serves it on a length, with the angle, the ball lands and nips away, beating the outside edge of Mendis who tries to defend inside the line.
Mendis and Sri Lanka are underway! A length ball, on middle, another inswinger. Mendis tucks it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
A sharp inswinger now. Length and outside off, it nips back in drastically. Mendis defends it out.
Length ball, well outside off for Mendis to make a leave.
Length ball, outside off. Mendis taps it late and to gully. Good fielding there by Hanuma Vihari.
A length ball, shaping outside off and holds its line off the deck. Mendis leaves it alone.
We are back. The players are out in the middle. Lahiru Thirimanne and Dimuth Karunaratne are the openers and Jasprit Bumrah has the new pink-ball in his hand.
... Fourth innings...

Shreyas Iyer and Ravindra Jadeja resumed their innings in this last session but Jadeja fell quickly. Iyer held one end and hit some valuable blows along with cameos from Ashwin and Shami. They have got a very good lead and Rohit Sharma will trust his bowling department whole-heartedly to go through the Lankan batting lineup. The chase coming your way shortly....

Here comes the declaration! Meanwhile, Suranga Lakmal gets a guard of honor as this is his last international game for Sri Lanka. So, a big target for Sri Lanka.
