They need 447 runs to level this Test series. Time will not be an issue but it will be a question of courage and intent. They are coming up against an aggressive bowling line up though. In terms of bowling, Sri Lanka did really well, other than Vishwa Fernando, all the other wickets went to the spinners. They were much more disciplined this time, especially Praveen Jayawickrama who ended with 4 wickets.

OUT! TIMBER! Too close to cut and Patel departs! This is a quicker ball, on a length, around off that goes on with the arm. Patel stays back to cut but he misses and the ball crashes onto his off pole. India declare their innings at 303/9.
Commentary.Howout: b Lasith Embuldeniya

Commentary.Commentary: Tosses it up, on middle. Axar Patel flicks it to mid-wicket. Not in the gap though!
Rishabh Pant is standing with his keeping pads on. Declaration first or Sri Lanka will bundle India out?
This is darted on the pads. Axar Patel tucks it wide of square leg and comes back for the second run.
Flatter and quicker, on off. Patel taps it behind square on the off side for a brace. 300 up for India!
A loopy ball, outside off. Patel pushes it back to the bowler.
Floated, full and outside off. Shami looks to heave it across the line but he misses.
SIX! CLUBBED! This is tossed up, in the slot, around middle. Shami whacks it way over long on and fetches himself a biggie.
Tosses it up, on middle. Patel nudges it towards deep mid-wicket and takes a run.
FOUR! Short and wide, outside off. Patel stays back and cuts it through the vacant point region for a boundary.
Tossed up, outside off. Shami looks to slog but he gets a thick inside edge towards fine leg for a run.
FOUR! A back foot punch from Shami! Flatter ball, going on with the angle from middle. Shami stays back and flicks it wide of mid on for a boundary.
Floated, full and around off. Patel prods and wrists it to short leg.
Shorter in length, outside off. Shami cuts it to point and takes a single.
A quicker ball, shorter in length, around off. Mohammed Shami hangs back to pull but he gets an inside edge onto his pad.
FOUR! This is tossed up, around middle. Shami sits back and flicks it through the vacant mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Flatter ball, on a length, outside off. Mohammed Shami looks to block but the ball spins past his outside edge.
Mohammed Shami walks out.
Review! Shreyas Iyer took a long time before he took the review. UltraEdge shows no bat. Meanwhile, Iyer is already walking back. Three reds and he continues his walk back.

OUT! LBW! Lasith Embuldeniya strikes from the other end and India lose their eighth wicket. Embuldeniya serves a quicker ball, on a length that goes on with the arm from middle. Iyer prods to block but he misses and gets hit on his pad. Sri Lanka appeal and up goes the umpire's finger. Iyer decides to review it but it is three reds on the Ball Tracker and Iyer is a goner!
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Lasith Embuldeniya

Commentary.Commentary: Shorter in length, around off. Patel gets back in his crease and defends it onto the deck.
Fuller in length, well outside off. Patel gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks it.
Axar Patel comes in. A short leg, catching mid-wicket, leg slip and first slip in place.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Praveen Jayawickrama picks up his fourth wicket and it is Ravichandran Ashwin who takes the walk back to the pavilion now. This is a flatter ball, on a length, outside off. Ashwin hangs back to cut but the ball spins sharply and it goes off the outside edge towards Niroshan Dickwella behind the sticks who takes a sharp catch.
Commentary.Howout: c Niroshan Dickwella b Praveen Jayawickrama

Commentary.Commentary: Floated, on a length, around middle. Ashwin stays back and keeps it out.
Shorter in length, on middle. Iyer flicks it to deep mid-wicket and takes a single.
Flatter ball, around off. Iyer hangs back and blocks it.
Praveen Jayawickrama comes back to bowl.
Short of a length, on off. Ashwin punches it to covers.
Very full and on middle. Ashwin pushes it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Passes the stumps! A length ball, around off and it nips back in sharp. Ashwin looks to work it on the leg side but gets an inside edge past the leg stump for a boundary.
Length and on the pads, Iyer works it to deep square leg for a single.
Fuller ball, outside off. Iyer misses his push. The ball literally rolled to the keeper after hitting the deck.
On the pads, flicked to mid-wicket. A misfield there and a single is taken.

DRINKS! India continues to pile on runs and they are taking the game away from Sri Lanka. Iyer has been impressive yet again in this innings and a declaration might be on the cards anytime soon. Sri Lanka might have to negotiate a tricky little period with the bat before Stumps on Day 2.
On middle, fuller and defended out.
Very full and on off. Iyer comes down and punches it to cover.
Around off, pushed through covers for a single.
Four byes! Fuller and down the leg side. Ashwin misses his flick. The ball stays low and goes through the legs of the keeper for a boundary.
Shorter and outside off, cut away to deep point for a single.
Flatter and on off, Iyer, on the back foot, pushes back to the bowler.
Fuller ball, angling across, and nips away more. Ashwin drives through the line and misses.
On middle, on a length, tucked to deep square leg for a single.
Length and on middle. Iyer pushes it back to the bowler.
A single as this is pushed to point.
Full and on middle. Ashwin flicks it to the right of mid-wicket. Suranga Lakmal there dives and gets a hand to it. Two runs taken.
Length and on middle, tucked to the right of mid-wicket for a quick single.
Flatter, turning away and extra bounce as well. Ashwin keeps his hands down and lets it through.
Full and angling on leg. Ashwin wrists it to deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
On middle. Blocked out.
Tossed up, on middle. Ashwin again solidly defends it.
Length ball, on off. Ashwin skips down and looks to defend but gets hit on the pads.
Shorter ball, coming with the arm, around off. Ashwin cuts it very late to point.
On a length, on middle. Defended out.
FOUR! Controlled! Length ball, outside off. Iyer opens the face of the bat and guides it past second slip and gully for a boundary.
Full ball, very wide and it almost ends up outside the pitch. Iyer leaves it alone.
FOUR! Edgy! Fuller ball, angling outside off. Ashwin looks to drive but gets an outside edge over the slip cordon for a boundary.
A length ball, outside off. Ashwin punches it to deep cover for a single.
Touch fuller, outside off. Iyer dabs it to third man for a single.
A bit shorter in length, around off. Ravichandran Ashwin gets back in his crease and blocks it. A maiden over from Lasith Embuldeniya!
Floated, on a length, around off and spinning away late. Ashwin waits for the ball to turn and then taps it towards point.
Ashwin skips down the track and defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted ball, around off. Ashwin keeps it out off the front foot.
Tosses it up, just outside off and spinning away from the batter. Ashwin lets it be.
Floated, on a length, around off. Ashwin hangs back and pushes it to cover.
Short of a length, angling across the batter. Ashwin stays back and taps it past point. He gets off the mark with a run.
Ravichandran Ashwin is the new man in.

OUT! Chopped on! Vishwa Fernando strikes and this is a much-needed breakthrough for Sri Lanka! This is a length ball, jagging back in late from outside off. Jadeja stays back and looks to guide it through the slip cordon. He gets cramped for room and the ball hits him on his pad, then goes on to hit his bat, bounces off the deck and crashes onto the stumps. Jadeja looks gutted as he walks back to the pavilion.
Commentary.Howout: b Vishwa Fernando

Commentary.Commentary: Back of a length, around off. Ravindra Jadeja blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! Edgy! This is a full ball, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja looks to play it across the line but he misses and the ball goes off the outside edge through the slip cordon for a boundary.
Full and outside off. Shreyas Iyer works it to mid off and rotates the strike.

FOUR! Cut away! Short and outside off. Iyer hangs back and cuts it through point for a boundary. Fifty in both the innings for Iyer and he becomes only the tenth Indian to do so. What a fine player he is turning out to be for India!
Floated, full and on middle. Iyer eases it to long on for a single.
Review! Iyer takes the LBW decision upstairs. There was a clear inside edge as seen on the replay. Good review from Iyer.

NOT OUT! There is a clear inside edge and Iyer survives! This is a length ball, around off that goes on with the arm. Iyer prods to block but he gets an inside egde onto his pad. Sri Lanka appeal as they think that it hit the pad first. The umpire agrees and raises his finger. Iyer reviews it straightaway and the UltraEdge confirms that the ball hit the bat first and then the pad.
Tossed up, around off. Shreyas Iyer gets forward and defends it to the off side.
An overpitched ball, on middle. Shreyas Iyer keeps it out.
Fuller in length, around off. Shreyas Iyer blocks it off the front foot.
Floated, full and on off. Shreyas Iyer stays back to defend.
On a length, way outside off. Jadeja shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja does not bother playing at that one.
This is a length ball, well outside off. Jadeja lets it through to the keeper.
A slower ball, on a length, around off. Jadeja taps it wide of the point fielder and wants a run but is sent back by Iyer.
On a length, around middle. Jadeja stays back and defends it with soft hands behind square on the off side.
Full ball, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja leaves it alone.
Flighted ball, around off, Iyer gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks it.
Another deft touch from Iyer to this ball which is wide, outside off. He doesn't time it well though and manages only two this time around.
FOUR! Deft touch! Tossed up, well outside off. Iyer hangs back and guides it through the third man region for a boundary. That brings up the 50-run stand between Iyer and Jadeja!
Tossed up, full and outside off. Iyer pushes it back to the bowler.
Floated, full and on middle. Jadeja looks to play it across the line but it goes off the leading edge towards cover for a single.
Tosses it up, outside off. Iyer works it to long off for a single.
Way outside off. Jadeja thinks of playing at it but leaves it alone in the end.
Fuller ball, on off, pushed to covers.
Length ball, outside off. Iyer works it to point now for one.
Length ball, outside off. Jadeja guides it to deep point for a single.
Around off, Blocked out.
Length ball, on off, extra bounce and Jadeja gets back to defend.
Vishwa Fernando (4-1-15-0) is back on.
A single as this is pushed to long on.
Outside off. Iyer dabs it to backward point for a single.
Flatter and outside off. Iyer misses his cut this time.
Fuller, outside off. Iyer tries to play it down but misses.
FOUR! Slightly short, on middle, stays low but again Iyer picks it well and hits it to mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Fuller and on middle. Iyer picks the length quickly and lifts it well over mid on for a boundary.
Length and on off. Jadeja punches off the back foot to covers.
Length and on middle, flicked to square leg for one.
Length and on off. Iyer prods to defend and gets an outside edge to gully. All along the ground.
Length, outside off. Left alone.
Down the leg side, Iyer misses his flick.
Pitched up, on off. Iyer pushes it to covers.

Fulller and outside off, spinning in sharply. Jadeja gets his pad out to block it. An appeal but the turn might miss the leg stump. No, actually the replay shows the wickets were hitting. Another decision goes begging.
Full and on off. Jadeja leans and blocks it.
Shorter and well wide. Iyer cuts it to deep cover for a single.
Short, outside off and Iyer prods and leaves it.
Darted on the pads, flicked to deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Tossed up, full and on off, Iyer skips down and pushes it to covers.
Two leg byes! Fuller and angling down on the pads. Iyer misses his flick. It goes off the pads past diving Dickwella to fine leg for a leg bye.
Well outside off. Iyer offers no shot.
Lovely delivery! This one lands on off, skids through and comes in sharply. Iyer is squared up as he looks to defend and gets hit well high on the pads. An appeal but an ambitious one.
Angles a full ball, on middle. Iyer defends it solidly.
A length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Full and angling on middle, pushed to mid on for a quick single.

Another arm ball from Praveen Jayawickrama that goes on with the angle from leg. Shreyas Iyer stays back to flick but he misses and Niroshan Dickwella behind the sticks does well to grab it by bending low.
A quicker ball, going on with the arm from off. Iyer prods to defend but he gets an inside edge onto his pad.
Flighted ball, on a length, outside off. Iyer lets it be.
Floated, full and on middle. Shreyas Iyer keeps it out.
Tossed up, outside off. Shreyas Iyer looks for a reverse sweep but he misses and gets hit on his pad.

FOUR! Edgy! This is a quicker ball, on a length, around off. Iyer stays back to push it through the off side. The ball goes off the outside edge and Lahiru Thirimanne bends down late to grab it. It falls short of him and sneaks through his legs to race away to the fence.
Back of a length, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja leaves it alone.

FOUR! Edged but it races away to the fence! Had there been a second slip in place, Jadeja might have been in trouble. A full ball, just outside off, drawing Jadeje to press forward. Jadeja looks to defend off the front foot but it goes off the outside edge for a boundary
That stayed low! Fuller in length, angling in from outside off. Ravindra Jadeja prods to defend but the ball goes past his outside edge.
Pitches it up, around off. Jadeja covers the line of the ball and dabs it onto the deck.
Lakmal drags his length back, around off. Jadeja taps it to the off side, off the back foot.
Fuller in length, around off. Ravindra Jadeja prods and pushes it towards cover.
Suranga Lakmal to bowl from the other end.
Another ball that goes on with the angle from off and turns away sharply. Iyer sways away from the line of the ball in the end.
This is a flatter ball, on a length, just outside off. The ball spins past Iyer's blade as he tries to cut it.
Flighted delivery, around off. Shreyas Iyer leans and defends it.
FOUR! Punished by Iyer! A half-tracker, around off. Iyer rocks back and pulls it in front of square to bag a boundary. 200 comes up for India.
Another ball, full and around off. Iyer gets forward to block it.
Tosses it up, around off. Iyer keeps it out.
We are back for the final session. Ravindra Jadeja and Shreyas Iyer walk out in the middle. Praveen Jayawickrama to start with the ball.
...Day 2, Session 3...

It were the spinners again for Sri Lanka who took the wickets but they allowed each batter to score quick runs. Their fielding was also very poor while two reviews that would have given them a positive decision were not taken, so the skipper's decision-making can also be questioned. They would hope to at least reduce the scoring rate and take the remaining wickets as soon as possible. The final session will start at 7 pm IST (1.30 pm GMT). See you there!

Sri Lanka managed to take 4 wickets in this session but it is the runs that hurt them. India added 138 runs in this session and now lead by 342. Rohit and Vihari were proactive and started looking for boundaries. Although, Rohit fell just 4 runs short of his fifty. Kohli came in to bat with intent but deja vu was written for him on the cards. It was then the Pant show. He has played each game as if it is a T20I so far but never fails to make an impact. Now, Iyer and Jadeja are out there and they will look to stretch the lead further.
A flatter ball, on a length, around off. Jadeja punches it towards mid off and looks to steal a single but Iyer sends him back in time. That will be Dinner on Day 2!
A low full toss, outside off. Shreyas Iyer drills it to deep cover and hands the strike back to Jadeja!
Shorter in length and outside off. Shreyas Iyer mistimes his cut shot towards the cover fielder.
Iyer withdraws just when Lasith Embuldeniya delivers it. Looks like some bees near his eyes.
Flatter and quicker, around leg. Ravindra Jadeja tucks it around the corner for a single.
Review time! India take a review for LBW. No bat clearly. Ball Tracking shows impact outside off and the wickets hitting so the on-field decision is changed.

NOT OUT! Good review from Jadeja! Another ball, that turns back in sharply from outside off. Ravindra Jadeja hangs back and looks to flick but he misses and gets hit on his pad. Lasith Embuldeniya appeals and the umpire raises his finger. Jadeja though reviews it straightaway and the Ball Tracker shows that the impact is outside off. The on-field decision needs to be overturned!
Turn and bounce yet again for Lasith Embuldeniya! This is a flatter ball, outside off and spinning in. Jadeja stays back and wrists it to the leg side.
Lasith Embuldeniya to bowl what could be the final over before Dinner.
Floated, full and around middle. Jadeja prods and tucks it towards the square leg fielder.
Excellent delivery! This is a quicker ball, on a length, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja plays for the turn but the ball doesn't spin and goes straight past the outside edge of Jadeja.
This is a flatter ball, turning in from outside off. Ravindra Jadeja stays back and pushes it back to the bowler.
Tossed up, on middle. Blocked out.
Floated, full and around off. Ravindra Jadeja blocks it off the front foot.
Tosses it up, full and outside off. Ravindra Jadeja prods and lets it be.
Good-length delivery, around off. Ravindra Jadeja hangs back and defends it to the off side.
A slower ball, fuller in length and outside off. Shreyas Iyer looks to play at it at first but leaves it in the end.
Pitches it up, around middle. Ravindra Jadeja tucks it wide of mid on and takes a single.
A full ball, well outside off. Ravindra Jadeja does not offer any shot to that one.
This is darted on the pads. Jadeja flicks it through square leg and comes back for the second run.
Fuller in length, well outside off. Ravindra Jadeja lets it sail through to the keeper.
Shorter in length, outside off. Shreyas Iyer rocks back and cuts it wide of deep cover for a brace.
Floated, full and around off. Shreyas Iyer pushes it towards cover.
Tosses it up, on a length, just outside off and spinning away from the batter. Shreyas Iyer prods to defend but the ball beats his outside edge.
Tosses it up, around off. Jadeja defends it to the off side and rotates the strike.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Shreyas Iyer taps it wide of point and takes a single.
An overpitched ball, on middle. Shreyas Iyer digs it out towards mid-wicket.
Fuller in length, around middle. Ravindra Jadeja gets solid in his front foot defence.
A length ball, angling in from off. Ravindra Jadeja keeps it out.
FOUR! Short and wide, outside off. Jadeja hangs back and cuts it through the vacant point region for a boundary. Easy pickings for Jadeja!
Back of a length, around off. Jadeja blocks it.
A full ball, angling in from middle. Iyer flicks it to fine leg for a run.
Fuller in length, on middle. Shreyas Iyer flicks it to mid-wicket. Not in the gap though!
Ravindra Jadeja comes in now.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Rishabh Pant looks for yet another big one but holes out in doing so! Tossed up delivery, outside off. Pant skips down and looks to go downtown. It goes off the toe end of the bat, high in the air, to the right of the bowler. Praveen Jayawickrama runs there, settles under it and takes it with ease. End of a brilliant innings from the southpaw!
Commentary.Howout: c & b Praveen Jayawickrama

Commentary.Commentary: Review! Sri Lanka take an LBW decision upstairs. No bat there as Pant offered no shot.  Ball Tracking shows wickets missing and Pant survives.

NOT OUT! This is a loopy ball, well outside off that turns in sharply. Pant shuffles across and pads it away. Praveen Jayawickrama appeals and the umpire says no. Dimuth Karunaratne opts for a review but the Ball Tracker suggests that the ball would have missed the off stump.
Flatter ball, turning in from outside off. Rishabh Pant defends it off the back foot.

FOUR! Whacked! FIFTY for Pant, off just 28 balls! This is a full ball, well outside off. Rishabh Pant reaches out and smacks it through the cover region for a boundary. This is the fastest fifty by an Indian in Test cricket.
Looped up, full and outside off. Rishabh Pant gets to the pitch of the ball and manages to block it awkwardly in the end.
Floated, full and around off. Iyer taps it behind square on the off side and takes a run.
A short ball, on middle. Shreyas Iyer swivels and pulls it along the ground towards deep square leg for a run.
FOUR! Poor ball from Lakmal and Iyer pounces on it! Back of a length, angling in from middle. Shreyas Iyer stays back and just helps it on its way through fine leg for a boundary.
Good-length delivery, around off. Rishabh Pant taps it to the off side and takes a single.
The umpires are having a word with Pant. He is standing way out of his crease and asking him to stand away from the danger area.
A slower ball, on a length, outside off. Rishabh Pant does not pick the slower ball and the ball beats his outside edge.
A yorker-length ball, around off. Rishabh Pant digs it out.
FOUR! Pant comes down the track and smashes it. A full ball, around off. Rishabh Pant steps down and whacks it through the mid off region for a boundary.
Suranga Lakmal is back for another spell.
Two byes! Full, outside off and moving away. Iyer swings and misses. The keeper fumbles and the ball goes past first slip for a couple of runs.
Review! Sri Lanka opt for a review for caught behind! The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows that the ball clipped only the pad and not the bat before going through to the keeper.

NOT OUT! Jayawickrama angles a length ball, down the leg side. Iyer looks to flick but seems to miss it. The ball did take a deflection on its way to the keeper and Dickwella thinks it is off the blade. He convinces his skipper to take it upstairs. UltraEdge shows nothing as the ball passes the bat.
Quicker ball, on the pads. Kept out.
An arm ball, straying around off. Iyer gets low to defend.
Fuller and on off, driven to deep covers for a single.
Dimuth Karunaratne having a word with Praveen Jayawickrama.
Down the leg side, swept to deep square leg for one more.
Tossed up, angling on leg. Iyer plays it late to deep square and rotates the strike.
Full and on middle, pushed to mid-wicket.
Short, Pant again waits on the back foot, to pull it to square on the leg side. A single.
FOUR! Short and well wide outside off. Pant hangs on the back foot to cut it through point for a boundary. India stretch their lead to 306 runs.
On middle. Pant comes forward to defend.
Length and on off. Iyer punches it through covers. Praveen Jayawickrama who is not fully fit, gives a chase and flicks it back to save a single.
FOUR! Short and angling down. Pant pulls it hard and past the diving fielder in the deep for a boundary.
On middle, tucked to mid-wicket.

Was that a chance? Quicker one on the pads. Pant comes down the track and looks to flick but misses. The ball lobs wide of the keeper. There was a stumping chance but needed some stopping from Dickwella.
FOUR! This is full and on middle. Pant paddles it aerially and past leg slip for a boundary.
Shorter and angling on the pads. Pant misses his flick.
Tossed up, on off, played to the right of Praveen.
Floated, full and on off, pushed through covers for one run.
On middle. Defended out.
Pant tries to play this late but hits it straight to point.
An arm ball, on leg. Pant waits on the back foot and flicks it through his legs to deep square leg for a brace.
FOUR! Pant playing quickly here! Fuller and outside off. Pant reverse sweeps it to point for a boundary.
Way outside off, driven to deep point for a single.
On middle, Iyer wrists it to mid-wicket for one.
Full and on off, pushed to covers.
Shreyas Iyer is the new batter in.

OUT! LBW! Just the way he got out in the first innings. It is deja vu for Virat Kohli! Bengaluru goes quiet yet again. Tossed up, full and around off, it lands and turns back in but does not bounce much. Virat Kohli rocks on the back foot to flick it but the ball stays low and gets hit on the pad. An appeal and up goes the finger. Virat Kohli yet again, gazes at the pitch and thinks for a moment to review but doesn't take it and walks back to the hut.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Praveen Jayawickrama

Commentary.Commentary: Kohli tries to cut this one but the ball did not bounce much, misses.
Tossed up, on off. Kohli plays it late and past gully but for no run.
Full and on off, pushed wide of the mid off fielder.

DRINKS! Sri Lanka have managed to pick a couple of wickets in this session but the Indian batters have changed gears and both Virat Kohli and Rishabh Pant have come out with positive intent. Sri Lanka need to keep chipping with wickets and make sure that they do not leak runs.
SIX! It is the Pant show! Tossed up, around off. Pant comes down the track and lifts it very high and clears the long off field by inches. The fielder there watches it sail over his head.

FOUR! A huge appeal for LBW but not given! A slider, comes with an angle, short and on middle. Pant rocks on the back foot and cuts it late to backward point for a  boundary. They think of taking a review but Dhananjaya de Silva says no.
Tossed up, on middle. Front foot defense from Pant.
Full ball, on off. Virat bunts it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Short ball, lands and spins away. Pant works it to point for a run.
Full and on off, stays low and Kohli flicks it to square leg for a single.
Full and sliding down the leg side. Pant fails to connect and the ball goes past the keeper and in between the legs of leg slip for a couple of runs. Given as runs means there was some bat on it.
SIX! Pant takes off! Fuller and on off. Pant steps down and heaves it well over mid-wicket for a biggie.
Short and outside off. Kohli cuts it to point for one more.
Full and on off. Kohli plays it to point.
Full and way outside off, dragged to deep square leg for a single.
Rishabh Pant walks out to bat.

OUT! BOWLED!  Vihari goes now. An arm ball, on a length and landing around off. Hanuma Vihari looks to sweep but misses and the ball rattles to hit the off stumps. Praveen Jayawickrama is limping as he tries to celebrate but he has been wonderful so far.
Commentary.Howout: b Praveen Jayawickrama

Commentary.Commentary: A full toss, on middle, pushed to long on for a single.
Around off. Blocked out.
Shorter, the ball grips and Vihari blocks it on the back foot.
Full ball, flighted on off. Vihari reverse sweeps it to deep backward point where Lasith Embuldeniya makes a superb stop to save a couple of runs.
Shorter and outside off, Kohli slaps it to deep cover for a single.
FOUR! Kohli playing with intent! Full and on middle. Kohli skips down and tonks it straight for a boundary
Full, slower and outside off. Vihari tries to defend inside the line.
Length and on off. Virat punches it through covers for a single.
Flatter and on off. Virat plays it late to third man for a couple of runs.
Full and on middle, whipped to deep mid-wicket for three runs.

A slider, angling around middle and leg. Vihari rocks back to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. A huge appeal but the umpire thinks it is going down. The replay shows the wickets were hitting. Another chance goes begging.
Fuller and outside off. Vihari presses forward to defend but gets an outside edge past gully for a brace.
Another solid block from Kohli, on the front foot.
Full and on off. Defended out.
Slightly short, on middle. Kohli pays with the spin to fine leg and the fielder does well to save a couple of runs in the deep.
Full and on off. Kohli lunges to defend.
Virat Kohli walks out to bat at number 4.

OUT! TAKEN! Finally, Sri Lanka have a breakthrough. Rohit Sharma had enough of defensive shots and went for a big one but holes out in the deep. Tossed up, full and on off. Rohit Sharma comes down the track but does not reach to the pitch of the ball. He still goes with the heave, to long on where Angelo Mathews takes it.
Commentary.Howout: c Angelo Mathews b Dhananjaya de Silva

Commentary.Commentary: Beaten! Tossed up, slower and outside off. Rohit prods to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Another ball, well outside off. Hanuma Vihari lets it through to the keeper.
This is a loopy ball, on middle. Hanuma Vihari defends it.
Slower through the air, outside off. Hanuma Vihari lets it be.
An inside edge saves Vihari! This is a flatter ball, going on with the angle from middle. Hanuma Vihari looks to block off the front foot but he gets an inside edge onto his pad.
Full and outside off. Hanuma Vihari defends it to the off side.
Shorter in length, around off. Hanuma Vihari keeps it out.
A quicker ball, darted on the pads. Rohit Sharma looks to sweep but he misses and gets hit on his pad.
BEATEN! This is a flatter ball, on a length and outside off. Rohit Sharma plays for the turn but the ball beats his outside edge.
This is darted on the pads. Hanuma Vihari eases it to long on for a single.
Flatter ball, around off. Hanuma Vihari defends it to the off side.
Tossed up, around off. Hanuma Vihari blocks it out.
Aerial but safe! Floated, full and outside off. Rohit Sharma mistimes his sweep wide of the deep square leg fielder for a single.
Tossed up, full and outside off. Hanuma Vihari leaves it alone.
Nicely played! Slightly shorter in length, on middle. Rohit Sharma flicks it wide of mid on. The fielder there cuts it off and the batters take three runs.
Floated, full and on middle. Rohit Sharma kneels and paddles it to fine leg for a brace.
An overpitched ball, full and outside off. Hanuma Vihari drills it to long off for a single.
Slower through the air, on a length, around off. Hanuma Vihari defends it to the off side.
Tossed up, outside off. Hanuma Vihari tries to defend it off the front foot but he misses.
Fuller in length, outside off. Rohit Sharma gets forward and defends it.
Rohit comes down the track and looks to block this flatter ball but he misses and gets hit on his pad.
This is a quicker ball, on middle. Rohit Sharma dabs it onto the deck.
Floated, fuller and outside off. Hanuma Vihari sweeps it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Tossed up, outside off. Rohit Sharma sweeps it towards deep square leg for one run.
Floated, around off. Rohit Sharma keeps it out off the front foot.
Dhananjaya de Silva is back on.
This is a flatter ball, well outside off. Hanuma Vihari lets it sail through to the keeper.
That one turns sharply! Flatter and quicker, on a length, outside off and turning away late. Hanuma Vihari leaves it alone.
Slower through the air, around off. Hanuma Vihari keeps it out.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Rohit taps it behind square on the off side and takes a single.
Floated, full and outside off. Rohit Sharma does not bother playing at that one.
Fuller in length, outside off. Rohit Sharma drives but straight to the cover fielder.
Tossed up, outside off. Hanuma Vihari leaves it alone.
This is darted on the pads. Hanuma Vihari tickles it towards fine leg and collects a couple of runs.
Nicely tossed up, around middle. Hanuma Vihari defends it with ease.
Floated, full and outside off. Hanuma Vihari lets it be.
FOUR! Nicely played! A full ball, on middle. Hanuma Vihari flicks it through the mid-wicket region and bags a boundary.
BEATEN! Tosses it up, full and around off. Hanuma Vihari tries to block but it beats his outside edge.
Full and on middle. Rohit Sharma blocks it out.
On a length, around middle. Rohit Sharma tucks it to mid-wicket.
Sharp turn! A flatter ball, around off and turning away late. Rohit Sharma gets forward to defend but the ball beats his outside edge.
Full and outside off. Hanuma Vihari drills it to long off and rotates the strike.
This is darted on the pads. Rohit Sharma tucks it to mid-wicket for a run.
BEATEN! Floated, on a length, just outside off and spinning away late. Rohit Sharma tries to block but the ball beats his outside edge.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Hanuma Vihari rocks back and blocks it.
Floated, full and around off. Hanuma Vihari leans and defends it to cover.
This one goes on with the arm, around middle. Hanuma Vihari pushes it to middle.
Full and outside off. Hanuma Vihari blocks it to the off side.
Floated, on a length, around off. Hanuma Vihari leans and blocks it.

Fuller in length, just outside off. Rohit Sharma gets to the pitch of the ball and dabs it onto the deck.

Right then! Rohit Sharma collects the trophy and as usual, hands it over to the youngsters in the team. He moves aside and the celebrations begin. That is all we have from this Test match as well as the series. We hope that you enjoyed the coverage. There is a lot of cricketing action happening around the globe for you to cheer. But from here, it is goodbye!

Rohit Sharma, the victorious skipper of India, says it's been a good run so far. Adds that Ravindra Jadeja is getting better and better every day and is a gun on the field as well, he is happy to have him. On Shreyas Iyer, he says that he is grabbing his opportunity and is carrying his form in each format. Tells, he was filling the big shoes of Pujara and Rahane and he has done brilliantly so far. On Rishabh Pant, Rohit says that he is getting better every day as well. During the England series as well, it was his approach and confidence that helps him to get better. On Ravichandran Ashwin, he feels he is one of the greats of the game and laughs by saying he has many years left in him. Mentions, it was the third pink-ball match in India and they are still learning to play that. Appreciates the crowd in the end.

Rishabh Pant is the PLAYER OF THE SERIES. He says, he enjoys both batting and keeping and needs to evolve and improve in each game. Adds that the wicket was difficult to bat on, so he thought of scoring quick runs. Tells that he is happy to bat wherever the management wants. Mentions that he is more confident about his keeping now.

Shreyas Iyer is the PLAYER OF THE MATCH. He says that when he saw the batters struggling, he made sure that he will take on the bowlers and play with their minds. Adds that he is really happy with the score that he got and is happy that it came in a winning cause. Tells that he has no regrets and is enjoying his batting. Says that he always wanted to play Test cricket for India and feels lucky to be playing alongside the greats of the game.

Dimuth Karunaratne, the skipper of Sri Lanka, says he would have been happier if they won the match. Adds that he was confident to make a big score here. Tells that they batted well in patches and in bowling as well, they gave away many loose balls. When asked about Suranga Lakmal, he says that he was one of the best bowlers he has seen and wishes good luck to him in the county.
... THE PRESENTATION ...

Axar Patel is up for a chat as well. He laughs and says he does not think too much as he knows that Jadeja and Ashwin will do most of the work. Adds that he asks other bowlers regarding what kind of pace is suitable on each wicket. He wishes the best to Ashwin who will play for another team in the upcoming Indian T20 League.

Ravichandran Ashwin is up for a quick chat. He says, he does not think much about his accomplishments. Adds, it was a challenge as they were playing a pink-ball Test after a long time. He was enjoying his bowling and was taking time to settle in. Tells that he works hard before delivering the ball. Mentions that Ahmedabad's pitch had more bounce, while here there was more spin. He also appreciates Dimuth Karunaratne's batting. On the wicket of Kusal Mendis, he says they had runs on the board and he was trying different things to take his wicket and it was one of those days where it worked for him.

It was a Test that was dominated by the bowlers, in spite of those knocks from Shreyas Iyer and Dimuth Karunaratne. India opted to bat first on a slow track and it was Shreyas Iyer and Rishabh Pant who made sure that they post a competitive total on the board. Then, it was the Indian bowlers who bundled out Sri Lanka for their second-lowest score against the hosts in Test cricket. They conceded a lead of 143 runs in the first innings and India took full advantage of that in their second innings. The Indian batters contributed well in the second innings as they set a huge target of 447 runs in front of Sri Lanka. Well, chasing those many runs on such a tricky surface was always going to be a challenge. Dimuth Karunaratne and Kusal Mendis came out with intent but they didn't get much help from their teammates. As a result, Sri Lanka fell way short of the target but Dimuth Karunaratne's hundred will surely go down as one of the finest knocks played on Indian soil.

India had to pick 6 wickets in the second session to win the match and their bowling attack has been sensational to wrap things up rather quickly. Although, it was Dimuth Karunaratne who stood strong in between India's victory and it was one of the best knocks played on a tricky wicket. It was Ravichandran Ashwin who picked up four wickets while Jasprit Bumrah finished with three wickets to his name. Karunaratne was delaying team India's win but then came Bumrah who knocked his middle stump over andthen, it was only a matter of time before they were bowled out. The only positive for Sri Lanka apart from Dimuth Karunaratne's hundred was that they went past the 200-run mark for the first time in the series.

Another thumping win for India as they defeat Sri Lanka by a whopping 238 runs and seal the Test series 2-0. They have outplayed the Lankans in this Test as well as the series and apart from Dimuth Karunaratne's scintillating hundred, nothing has gone the tourists' way in this Test. India have been just too good for their opposition and they also grab 12 crucial points in the World Test Championship cycle.

Right then! Sri Lanka has shown some resistance but on this kind of a track, one wicket brings two and India would be keen to make early inroads post-Tea break. Will Sri Lanka go past the 200-run mark for the first time in this Test series? Do join us for the second session which could also turn out to be the last of this series and it begins at 4.20 pm IST (10.50 am GMT).

Kusal Mendis and Dimuth Karunaratne continued from where they left off on Day 2 and the Lankans got off to a brisk start. Both Karunaratne and Mendis were playing their shots and looked at ease for a while. Although, Mendis perished on 54 and then the tourists lost wickets in quick succession. Karunaratne is leading from the front and he has shown some resistance against the Indian bowlers. For India, it was the spin-duo of Ravichandran Ashwin and Ravindra Jadeja who got into the wickets column but Sri Lanka would be reasonably happy with the kind of fight they are showing on such a tricky pitch.

Sri Lanka have finally shown some intent with the bat in this series. The overnight batters, Kusal Mendis and skipper, Dimuth Karunaratne came out with good, positive intent of scoring runs and the tourists have managed to score 123 runs in the first session of Day 3, although, at the cost of three wickets.

Hello and a warm welcome to the action of Day 3 between India and Sri Lanka. What is called a moving day can prove to be the final day of the match. The equation is very simple, India need 9 wickets to win while Sri Lanka need 419 runs with an ample amount of time. Dimuth Karunaratne and Kusal Mendis played the tricky small period on Day 2 very nicely and did well to close the day without any more damage. They will look to have a positive opening hour while India will come out with full force and look to bundle the visitors out.
... Day 3, Session 1...

Right then! Here is the equation going into Day 3 of this Test - Sri Lanka need 419 runs to win while India require 9 wickets to win this Test as well as the series. Sri Lanka will need to bat out of their skins going ahead in this Test and India will look to make early inroads in the first session on Day 3 and keep the visitors at bay. Will India pick 9 wickets on Day 3 itself and seal the series? We shall find that soon. The action on Day 3 begins at 2 pm IST (8.30 am GMT). But as usual, our buildup will begin much earlier. Do join us for the same. Till then, Adios!

Hanuma Vihari is up for a chat. He says the pitch was quite challenging but he thinks they batted well. Adds that their bowling was good as well and feels it will be hard for Sri Lanka and is confident that they will take the remaining wickets quickly. Tells that he should have batted with more patience and speaking about the pitch, he thinks in both the innings it was challenging. Mentions that he waited for a particular delivery to score on. Says that they had no plans of bowling in the final session but because they lost wickets, they had a go in the last 35-40 minutes.

Earlier in the day, it was Jasprit Bumrah and Ravichandran Ashwin who wrapped things up quickly for India, and Sri Lanka were bowled out for their second-lowest total against India in Test cricket. They conceded a first innings lead of 143 runs and then it was onto their bowlers to make sure that they do not let the hosts run away with the game. Although, they weren't upto the mark as their bowlers were inconsistent and managed to keep things tight only for a while. Coming to India's batting - There were some good contributions from Rohit Sharma and Hanuma Vihari but India's youngsters, Rishabh Pant and Shreyas Iyer stole the show yet again. Both of them scored fifties and almost batted Sri Lanka out of this Test. Sri Lanka were set a target of 447 runs and they didn't get off to a great start as they lost their opener Lahiru Thirimanne for a duck. Jasprit Bumrah and Mohammed Shami made the new ball talk yet again but Dimuth Karunaratne and Kusal Mendis ensured that Sri Lanka do not lose any more wickets heading into Day 3.

Another enthralling day of this pink-ball Test comes to an end. Just like Day 1, Day 2 has also been all about India as Sri Lanka have been outplayed by a strong Indian side. The Lankans have a mountain to climb now and their batters have their task cut out going into Day 3. India will be happy to get a wicket before Stumps but they would have certainly liked a couple more.
